DESCRIPTION:In partnership with the Dharma Rain Zen Center with support by 
 East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation District\, Friends of Trees is hon
 ored to be part of the initial native plant revegetation work occurring in 
 this neglected parcel of North East Portland.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45a
 m to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly
  at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well 
 as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wea
 ring sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested 
 for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.
 org/volunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.   Please c
 ontact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need mor
 e information.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T154537Z
LOCATION:8510 NE Siskiyou\, Portland\, OR 97220
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Dharma Rain Zen Center Planting\, NE Portland
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
