UID:67qtigdj3oqkqkf93coek4sst9@google.com
CREATED:20220202T234121Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u>Your help is needed to mulch hundreds 
 of native trees and shrubs that were planted this past winter at this 2 acr
 e natural area site abutting the Columba Slough! We may also take out some 
 weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>Note: there will be no t
 ree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u>&nbsp
 \;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tree Care events he
 lp to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer
  months ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registr
 ation is closed at this time but there is still space available at this eve
 nt!&nbsp\; Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.</p><b>Please 
 arrive by 9:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\, Tree Care activities st
 art promptly at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all 
 you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes 
 or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<p><b>
 Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a
  parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and 
 will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwa
 iver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><
 p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is o
 ur number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all peopl
 e at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are i
 neligible\, such as children younger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear 
 a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distanc
 e from others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and 
 any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your 
 household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\
 ;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequentl
 y Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &n
 bsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out 
 our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer 
 FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You ca
 n reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forwa
 rd to working together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partners
 hip with Portland OIC and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation with support fro
 m the Port of Portland\, East Multnomah Soil &amp\; Water Conservation Dist
 rict\, and the National Fish &amp\; Wildlife Foundation to restore this two
  acre parcel of the Slough.&nbsp\;</p><p><i>Friends of Trees continues to f
 ollow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health 
 Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will 
 cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><br></p><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230103T120105Z
LOCATION:11058 NE Simpson St\, Portland\, OR 97220\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Columbia Slough Natural Area Tree Care (NE Portland)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
