DESCRIPTION:Help our newly planted trees and shrubs get a jump on the compe
 tition - invasives! You'll learn native plant identification and care techn
 iques with Friends of Trees staffers and volunteers as we hand remove invas
 ive plant species. \nVolunteers are welcome to come early at 8 am and have 
 breakfast as part of the City of Wilsonville's WERK's Volunteer Day.  Break
 fast will be served at the Wilsonville Community Center.\nOur Tree Care eve
 nt will start at 9 am near the Community Garden's in Memorial Park.  Go to 
 the intersection of SW Wilsonville Road and SW Kolbe Ln\, turn down Kolbe L
 n\, and find parking where Koble dead ends at the pedestrian bridge.\nFor m
 ore information about these work parties\, please contact Greg Tudor at Gre
 gT@FriendsofTrees.org\, or call 503-282-8846 ext. 12.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T154537Z
LOCATION:7800 SW Wilsonville Road\, Wilsonville OR 97070
