DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and our partners to celebrate National Po
 llinators Week this June! <br><br>This is the first of two community worksh
 ops to learn about local pollinators\, how to steward healthy pollinator ha
 bitats\, and get a chance to see these awesome flora and fauna in action. T
 his workshop is free to the public\, and fully outdoors. Materials will be 
 provided for participants\, just bring yourself!<br><br><b>How do I registe
 r? </b>Register by filling out <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511
 ?tfa_26=a0TPa00000AvfYe&tfa_2189=Pollinator%20Workshop\,%20Bethany&tfa_31=a
 0VPa000002asf3&tfa_45=%20at%20June%2017\,%202024%20at%204:00%20pm&tfa_2190=
 2024-06-17&tfa_49=2&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank">
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><u>this quick form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b>. <
 br><br>Prepare for a brief guided garden tour and to come home with a nativ
 e plant to steward healthy pollinator habitat in your local community here 
 in Washington County. <br><br>This workshop is made possible by funding fro
 m Tualatin Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District.
