DESCRIPTION:<span>============<br><br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this
  event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider joining an
 y of our other open plantings -- we hope to plant with you soon!<br></span>
 <br><span>============&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</span> <br><br>Your help is needed at 
 this work party where we will be removing weedy introduced plants and plant
 ing native trees and shrubs at the newly developed Gateway Green! Gateway G
 reen offers 25 acres of bike adventure fun. Opening in 2017 and offering a 
 variety of bike trail options\, we are excited to be part of the multi-part
 ner efforts to help revegetate the forested slope that borders the eastern 
 edge of this area.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Please note:</b>&nbsp\;<b>this park is 
 only accessible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. Please park at Gateway Transi
 t Center. There is an approximately 10 - 15 minute walk from the Gateway Tr
 ansit Center.&nbsp\;</b>Volunteers are encouraged to bike to the planting o
 r take public transportation to the transit center and walk from there. Tha
 nk you for supporting an alternative approach to arriving at this community
  event!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:30 am to find parking\, give yourself the
  10-15 min needed to walk to the site (see below)\, sign-in\, and enjoy som
 e breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts
  at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you ne
 ed to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\,
  and be ready to have fun! <br><br><br><b><u>Under age 18?</u></b> A signed
  youth waiver is required for you to volunteer: <b><a href="http://www.frie
