DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Your help is needed to plant hundreds of native trees and
  shrubs at the unique Gateway Green Park in NE Portland! </b>Help enhance t
 he natural area in this unique mountain-biking oasis situated in between I-
 84 and I-205. This event *would not be possible* without community support 
 - thanks for considering signing-up!<br></p><p><em>This park is only access
 ible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. There is an approximately 10 - 15 minute
  walk from the **SW corner** of the Fred Meyer parking lot (by the garden c
 enter) down the multi-use path to our planting site\, look for our signs. V
 olunteers are encouraged to bike to the planting or take public transportat
 ion to the transit center and walk from there.</em></p><p>*Please note this
  event starts 1 hour later than most of our plantings. <u>Please arrive by 
 9:45am</u> to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts 
 at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as 
 breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show
  up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to
  have fun!<b><br></b></p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration h
 as closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event\, please sim
 ply show up and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http:
 //friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a> signe
 d by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunt
 eer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to ass
 ist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u
 ><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look for
 ward to planting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event spo
 nsors <a href="https://www.nba.com/blazers/threesfortrees"><u>Portland Trai
 l Blazers &amp\; Daimler Truck North America</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p></p><
 hr /><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with <span>Friends of Gatew
 ay Green\, Portland Parks and Recreation\, and Portland OIC.</span></p>
