DESCRIPTION:This event is our first planting along the I-205 Multi-Use Path
  this year. We are very excited to continue reforesting the transportation 
 corridor that runs from the Columbia River in the North to the City of Glad
 stone in the south. Metro\, ODOT\, BES and EMSWCD are partnering with Frien
 ds of Trees to increase livability\, habitat and air quality along the I-20
 5 corridor.  Friends of Trees will provide morning refreshments\, gloves\, 
 tools\, and all necessary guidance. Please wear sturdy shoes and dress for 
 the weather.  \n\nPlease contact Andy Meeks at AndyM@FriendsofTrees.org or 
 503-282-8846 x24 for more information.\n\n*This event is affiliated with th
 e Alliance for Community Trees NeighborWoodsâ¢ Month.\n
