DESCRIPTION:<br>***********<br><br><b>This training is now <u>full and clos
 ed</u></b>\, we're grateful for the interest the community has shown in thi
 s leadership role!&nbsp\; Our next Crew Leader trainings will be in Fall 20
 20.&nbsp\; <i>Please let us know if you'd like to be added to a list that w
 e'll email when registration for these trainings opens! volunteer@friendsof
 trees.org</i><br><br><br>***********<br><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.
 org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" id="ow3960" __is_owner="true">
 Crew Leaders</a></b>&nbsp\;are trained volunteers who are crucial to planti
 ng trees properly and leading groups of volunteers from the public at our c
 ommunity planting events! Friends of Trees is aiming to plant tens of thous
 ands of native trees and shrubs at more than 50 events in parks and natural
  areas across the greater Portland Metro region. Help make those goals a re
 ality and register to become a Crew Leader!<br><br>The training is free (an
 d includes breakfast snacks\, lunch\, and a t-shirt!) but registration is r
 equired.<br><br>As part of this important role\, we expect all Crew Leaders
  to attend an additional 3-4 events February-May.&nbsp\; We're grateful for
  your commitment of time and energy to this important work!<br><br>Please c
 ontact Jenny or Pablo if you need more information: (503) 595-0213 //&nbsp\
 ;<a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org
 </a>. We look forward to answering any questions you may have!&nbsp\;&nbsp\
 ;
