DESCRIPTION:This event is in partnership with the City of Tualatin and Clea
 n Water Services. We will be planting native riparian species in and around
  the 8.5 acre Saum Creek wetland area.  \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to 
 be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9
 :00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gl
 oves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing 
 sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested for g
 roups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/v
 olunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so. Please contact 
 Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more infor
 mation.
