DESCRIPTION:============================================<br><b>Due to popul
 ar interest\, this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>.  We have a couple m
 ore events left the following Saturday that we would love for you to consid
 er. Our '25-26 season will begin again in the fall. Have a great spring/sum
 mer! :)<br>===========================================<br><br>Celebrate Ear
 th Week by mulching hundreds of native trees and shrubs that were planted t
 his past winter! We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if tim
 e allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this 
 is physically-demanding work</u> (great for folks looking for a work out!).
   Our stewardship events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival
  through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<p><b>Please arrive by 8:45am</b> 
 to find our tent and sign-in\, stewardship activities start promptly at 9:0
 0am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. All you need to do is show u
 p dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of 
 any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We
  request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a hre
 f="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> si
 gned by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Transit:</b><span> Bus Line 76 with
  a .7 mile walk.</span></p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check
  out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank
 "><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to ass
 ist!  Reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"
  target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>
 iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u>
 </a> We look forward to working together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you t
 o our event sponsors <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"
 ><u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u></a> &amp\; <a href="https:/
 /www.honltreecare.com/">Honl Tree Care</a>.</p><p>===</p><hr /><p>This even
 t is in partnership with City of Tualatin.<br></p>
