DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Out of an abundance of caution\, th
 is event is canceled due to continued frozen rain and icy road conditions. 
 </b>Please stay safe\, we hope to work with you again soon!</p><p><b>======
 ==</b></p><p><b>Thank you for considering signing-up for this unique event 
 with the goal of saving hundreds of young native plants and trees along the
  Salmonberry Trail Rails-to-Trails project!</b><span> We will be clearing t
 he decommissioned railroad in Banks in preparation for walking trails to be
  built\, and giving hundreds of young plants a second chance at life. Help 
 needed!</span><br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned
  a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\
 , and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot ch
 ocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing st
 urdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><
 span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian. 
  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <
 /span><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver fo
 rm</u></b></a><span> signed by their parent/guardian.</span><br></p><p><b>Q
 uestions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vol
 unteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u
 ></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volu
 nteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u
 ></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p
 ><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with <span>Clean W
 ater Services\, Salmonberry Trail Foundation\, Friends of Stub Stewart.</sp
 an></p>
