DESCRIPTION:Help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs tha
 t were planted this past winter at this special site park! We may also take
  out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there will be 
 no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u> 
 (great for folks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events help to 
 ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer month
 s ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>How do I register?  </b>Please simply show 
 up\, we'll see you Saturday! :)</p><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to fin
 d our tent and sign-in\, stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00am. 
 We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dre
 ssed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any k
 ind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><em>This park is only ac
 cessible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. There is an approximately 10 - 15 mi
 nute walk from the **SW corner** of the Fred Meyer parking lot (by the gard
 en center across from The Oregon Clinic) down the multi-use path to our pla
 nting site\, look for our signs. Volunteers are encouraged to bike to the p
 lanting or take public transportation to the transit center and walk from t
 here.</em></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under vo
 lunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their 
 own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youth
 waiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p></p><
 p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b>
 <u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a
 >.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>v
 olunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>
 Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://wyldcbd.com/" target="_blan
 k"><u><u><u>WYLD</u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><hr /><p>This event is in pa
 rtnership with Friends of Gateway Green\, POIC\, and Portland Parks &amp\; 
 Recreation.</p>
