DESCRIPTION:<b>Due to popular interest\, this event is now full and closed 
 for groups</b> Please consider our Oregon City neighborhood planting happen
 ing this same day/time or our future Beaverton plantings.  RSVPs are not re
 quired for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n
 \nFriends of Trees is working with Clean Water Services to restore the Chur
 chill Forest natural area to a diverse and healthy riparian forest and ephe
 meral wetland. This planting project is situated in the headwaters of Summe
 r Creek and will help to protect the uppermost section of the watershed by 
 planting a wide variety of native trees and shrubs. \n\nPlease arrive aroun
 d 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start p
 romptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, a
 s well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather 
 and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\nAre yo
 u under age 18 and planting without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href
 =http://www.friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>you
 th waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 
 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.\n\nDo not hesitate to reach 
 Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more inf
 ormation. We look forward to seeing you out in Beaverton!
