DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/
 crew-leader/"><b>Crew Leaders</b></a> are trained volunteers who are crucia
 l to planting trees properly and leading groups of volunteers from the publ
 ic at our community planting events! Friends of Trees is aiming to plant te
 ns of thousands of native trees and shrubs at more than 50 events in parks 
 and natural areas across the greater Portland Metro region. Help make those
  goals a reality and register to become a Crew Leader!<br><br>The training 
 is free (and includes breakfast snacks\, lunch\, and a t-shirt!) but regist
 ration is required.  <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/crew-leader-tra
 ining/">Register HERE</a></b> to train for this role\, space limited.<br><b
 r>Please contact Jenny or Pablo if you need more information: (503) 595-021
 3 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org</a>. We look forward to answering any questions you may have!<br><br>=
