DESCRIPTION:<b>Due to weather and the specific nature of this site\, this e
 vent is cancelled until further notice.  We apologize for this inconvenienc
 e!</b>\n\nJoin us at this tree care event as a part of our restoration effo
 rts at this 23 acre park in SE Portland. We will be spreading mulch and rem
 oving invasive weeds to prepare this site for this December's planting. Thi
 s event is in partnership with Portland Parks & Recreation and the Portland
  Parks Foundation as a part of Parke-Diem\, as well the Johnson Creek Water
 shed Council and is supported by the East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservati
 on District and Metro.\n\nVolunteers should come dressed for the weather an
 d wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! Friends of T
 rees will provides gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance.\n\n<b>Individual
 s and groups less than 5 people</b> are kindly requested to sign-up to atte
 nd this event through the <a href=https://fs22.formsite.com/parklandia/form
 3/index.html>Parke-Diem registration form</a>.\n\n<b>Groups larger than 5 p
 eople</b> can sign up via the <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteerin
 g/group-registration>Friends of Trees Group Registration form</a>.\n\nPleas
 e contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or nee
 d more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
