DESCRIPTION:===============<br><br>Due to popular interest our Autumn Creek
  planting is now <b>FULL and CLOSED</b>.&nbsp\; Thank you for your understa
 nding\, many of our Spring events do fill up 2-4 weeks in advance.&nbsp\; P
 lease consider joining any of our other open planting or tree care events!<
 br><br>===============<br><br>Friends of Trees is working with Clean Water 
 Services and the Autumn Creek HOA in NW Portland to restore this natural ar
 ea to a diverse and healthy forest. Come on out\, and help plant hundreds o
 f native trees and shrubs -- your help is what makes this community plantin
 g possible!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakf
 ast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts promptl
 y at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to 
 do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â
  and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A signed <a href="ht
 tps://wpdevfriendsoftrees-4977.kxcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Youth_W
 aiver.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you to voluntee
 r. We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><
 br>This planting is part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted 
 more than eight million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since
  2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, 
 other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners will be working 
 together this season to continue the success of this program.<br><br>Please
  contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>
  if you have questions or need any further information. We look forward to 
 seeing you out there!<br><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a hre
 f="https://www.portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank">PGE</a>.<br>===&nbsp\;
  &nbsp\;&nbsp\;
