DESCRIPTION:<p>==============</p><p><b>T<wbr><u></u><u></u>his event is now
 &nbsp\;<u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Thank you for helping care for tr
 ees during the month of May\, please check back in the Fall of 2021 for new
  planting opportunities! ===========<wbr><u></u><u></u>===</p><br>Your help
  is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that were planted t
 his past winter at this amazing park in East County! We may also take out s
 ome weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>Note: there will be 
 no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u>&
 nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tree Care event
 s help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry su
 mmer months ahead.<br><br><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b>&nbsp\;to find our 
 tent and sign-in\, Tree Care activities start promptly at 10:00am. We provi
 de gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed
  for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\
 , please!) and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbs
 p\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends
  of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events bring and wear a 
 face mask\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own hou
 sehold\, and follow a few other protocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a hre
 f="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Aske<u><
 /u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>d-Questions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; This event wi
 ll have 15-25 people total.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request th
 at youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u>.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will ne
 ed to include their parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>'s contact
  information when they register online.<br><br><b>Question<u></u><u></u><u>
 </u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u>s?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="htt
 ps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp
 \; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pablo\, a
 nd Carey at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>voluntee
 r@fr<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u>
 </u>g</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to seeing you out there!<br><br><i>Frie
 nds of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by
  the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not saf
 e to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pr
 e-registered.</i>
