DESCRIPTION:<p><b>====================</b></p><p><b>This event is now full 
 and closed</b>. Please consider our final Jackson Bottom event for the seas
 on on Saturday\, Nov 8th or any of our other events. <b></b></p><p><b>=====
 ================</b></p><p><b><br></b></p><p><b>Calling all nature lovers -
  your help needed to plant hundreds of native plants at Jackson Bottom Wetl
 ands Preserve! </b>Jackson Bottom is a 635-acre wetland complex on the Tual
 atin River that is designated as an Important Bird Area for both migrating 
 and non-migratory species.</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be 
 assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/te
 a/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather we
 aring sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><i>**Please n
 ote: there is a 10 minute walk from the parking area to where we'll be plan
 ting. Please plan your timing accordingly.</i></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> W
 e request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 
 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a
  href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u>yout
 h waiver form</u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><
 p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u>
 </u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cec
 e and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank
 "><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></a>\, 503-595-02
 13. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p><br>This 
 event is in partnership with the City of Hillsboro.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251008T000600Z
LOCATION:2600 SW Hillsboro Hwy\, Hillsboro\, OR 97123\, USA
