DESCRIPTION:Friends of Trees is partnering with the City of Salemâs Storm
 water Division and Parks Department to stabilize the stream banks along Pri
 ngle Creek and provide a natural buffer around the creek as it winds throug
 h this beautifully wooded park. This yearâs two plantings will focus on t
 he south end of the park where we will be expanding the riparian forest fro
 m the parking lot to the footbridge next to Judson Middle School\, and will
  be held in conjunction with the No Ivy Coalition. Bring your disc golf dis
 cs to play the challenging course that runs through the park after the plan
 ting! \n \nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a c
 rew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks a
 nd hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please co
 me dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have f
