DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Week by mulching hundreds of native trees and s
 hrubs that were planted this past winter! We may also take out some weedy i
 ntroduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-planting 
 at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u> (great for folks 
 looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events help to ensure the highes
 t level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><br><
 u></u><i>**This park is only accessible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. There
  is an approximately 10 - 15 minute walk from the **SW corner** of the Fred
  Meyer parking lot (by the garden center across from The Oregon Clinic) dow
 n the multi-use path to our planting site\, look for our signs. Volunteers 
 are encouraged to bike to the planting or take public transportation to the
  transit center and walk from there.**<br><u></u></i><p><b>How do I registe
 r? </b>Online registration has closed\, but there is still room at this eve
 nt.  Please simply show-up at 9:45am (note the walk/parking situation\, abo
 ve)\, and sign-in when you arrive!</p><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to 
 find our tent and sign-in\, stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00a
 m. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up 
 dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of an
 y kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We r
 equest that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 
 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href=
 "https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by t
 heir parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Transit:</b> <span>MAX Blue Line with a .2 m
 ile walk.</span></p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out ou
 r <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach Ce
 ce and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blan
 k"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u
 ></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward 
 to working together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <
 a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Portland Gen
 eral Electric</u></u></u></a> &amp\; <a href="https://www.honltreecare.com/
 " target="_blank"><u>Honl Tree Care</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p><hr />
 <p>This event is in partnership with Friends of Gateway Green\, Portland Pa
 rks &amp\; Recreation\, Portland OIC\, and Portland Parks Foundation.</p>
