DESCRIPTION:<p>==============</p><p><b>T<u></u>his event is now&nbsp\;<u>fu
 ll and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; We hope to work with you at another of our Sp
 ring Tree Care events!&nbsp\; Please consider any of the other open green '
 Tree Care' events in May.</p><p>===========<u></u>===</p><br>Celebrate Eart
 h Day by mulching hundreds of native trees and shrubs that were planted thi
 s past winter at this popular community park! We may also take out some wee
 dy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>Note: there will be no tree
 -planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u>&nbsp\;(
 great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tree Care events help 
 to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer mo
 nths ahead.<br><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of voluntee
 rs and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiri
 ng that all people at our events bring and wear a face mask\, respect 6' or
  more of distance from others not in their own household\, and follow a few
  other protocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees
 .org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Aske<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u
 >d-Questions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; This event will have 15-25 people tota
 l.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under vol
 unteer with a parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u><
 /u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>.&nbsp\; Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to include their paren
 t/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>'s contact information when they re
 gister online.<br><br><b>Question<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>s?&nbsp\;&nb
 sp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/v
 olunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy
  to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at&nbsp\;<a href
 ="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@fr<u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>g</b></a>&nbsp\;We lo
 ok forward to seeing you out there!<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to
  follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Healt
 h Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we wil
 l cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><i><br><
 /i><br>===<br>Thank you to our sponsors&nbsp\;<a href="https://onetreeplant
 ed.org/" id="ow584" __is_owner="true">One Tree Planted</a>!<br>==<u></u>=&n
