DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><b>Help is needed to plant hundreds of
  native trees and shrubs at Arrowhead Creek Park in Wilsonville!</b> Join F
 riends of Trees and the City of Wilsonville as we enhance the natural area 
 adjacent to the Wilsonville Water Treatment Plant. Thank you for your suppo
 rt -- this event *would not be possible* without you!<br><u></u><br><u></u>
 Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The pla
 nting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\,
  as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need t
 o do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and
  be ready to have fun!<u></u><br><br><b>How do I register?</b> Register by 
 filling out this&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T
 5G00000P0ZKC&tfa_2189=Arrowhead%20Creek%20Park%20planting\,%20Wilsonville&t
 fa_31=a0V5G00000UaYKA&tfa_45=Tree%20Planter\,%20%20at%20February%2011\,%202
 023%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_2190=2023-02-11&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=Standard%20FOT
 &tfa_51=offsite"><b>quick form</b></a>. Groups and individuals welcome!<br>
 <p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer 
 with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their ow
 n and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org
 /youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their 
 parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>requir
 e</u>&nbsp\;that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell 
 or have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 d
 ays of the event.&nbsp\; We&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-
 vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, an
 d respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\
 ; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&
 nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&n
 bsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@frien
 dsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&n
 bsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This event
  is in partnership with the City of Wilsonville<br></p><u></u><u></u></html
 -blob>
