 is yearâs <u></u>three<u></u> planting events at the Minto Island Conserv
 ation Area. We will be planting native trees and shrubs along the new multi
 -use path connecting Riverfront Park with the greater Minto Brown Island Pa
 rk. This event is partially funded with grants from Oregon Watershed Enhanc
 ement Board and Meyer Memorial Trust.<br><br>Please arrive by <u></u>8:45am
 <u></u> to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or ho
 t chocolate. Please note there will be a 10-15 min walk from the parking ar
 eas to the planting site.&nbsp\; The planting starts promptly at <u></u>9:0
 0am.<u></u> We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to d
 o is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â 
 and be ready to have fun! <br><br><b>How do I register?</b>&nbsp\;Registrat
 ion closes the day before the planting event\, but there still is a little 
