DESCRIPTION:This Planting is part of the Tree for All event and is in partn
 ership with the City of Beaverton and Clean Water Services. This is our thi
 rd year planting live stakes and bare root shrubs\, restoring the riparian 
 area along Summer Creek. The ambitious goal of Tree for All is to plant two
  million trees in the Tualatin River Valley in 20 years. \n\nPlease arrive 
 around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will st
 art promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffe
 e\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. This area will be wet - please 
 bring rubber boots if you have them! This planting is generously sponsored 
 by KIND.\n\nRSVPs are not required. Please contact Andy or Jenny at (503) 5
 95-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward
  to seeing you out there! 
