 \;</b>&nbsp\;Based on recent recommendations from public health officials\,
  we’re respecting their advice to create a pause in social gatherings and n
 ot voluntarily bringing a group of people together.&nbsp\; We sincerely apo
 logize for this inconvenience and hope to reunite with you under safer cond
 itions soon!<br><br><br>==========<u></u>=======&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Wh
 at about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our numb
 er one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at ou
 r events bring and wear a fabric face mask\, respect 6' or more of distance
  from others not in their own household\, bringing your own water bottle an
 d any other snacks or beverages you will need\,&nbsp\;and follow a few othe
 r protocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/
 volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Asked-Questions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\
 ;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volu
 nteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on th
