DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Help needed to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs 
 at our Lower Gales Creek planting site! </b></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am 
 to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. 
 We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast sn
 acks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed 
 for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<b
 r><br><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time
 \, but there is still room at this event. Please simply show up and sign-in
  at the welcome table when you arrive!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We reques
 t that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and o
 lder can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://
 friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a> signed 
 by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a 
 href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Voluntee
 r FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assis
 t!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><
 b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This event 
