DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Thanks to popular interes
 t in this event\, it is now <u>full and closed</u>. </b>Please consider any
  of our other open events\, including our next Forest Grove planting on Sat
 \, March 19th.&nbsp\; Thank you!</p><p><b>======</b></p><p><b>Help needed t
 o rescue native plants along the new Salmonberry Rails-to-Trails project!</
 b>&nbsp\;&nbsp\;The goal of this event is to rescue small native trees and 
 plants growing along the discontinued railroad tracks outside Banks\, OR. W
 e will dig them out of the tracks\, and they will be replanted at a later d
 ate at restoration sites around Washington County. Your help is needed to s
 ave these native plants before the paving begins!&nbsp\; Please note: we wi
 ll not be planting at this event.</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in 
 and be assigned a work crew. The event starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and instruction-- all you need to do is show up dressed for the w
 eather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>U
 nder age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a 
 parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and w
 ill need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwai
 ver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></
 p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff i
 s our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all pe
 ople at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who ar
 e ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immu
 nocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the 
 event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in the
 ir own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beve
 rages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell w
 ithin two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpag
 e</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p>
 <p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbs
 p\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\
 , and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volun
 teer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together 
 soon!<br></p><b><hr><br></b>This event is in partnership with the Friends o
 f Stub Stewart State Park and Clean Water Services.<br><br><i>Friends of Tr
 ees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC 
 and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host
  events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registe
 red.</i></html-blob>
