 emove invasive English ivy from Memorial Park.  We will be working near the
  forest shelter in the park near the banks of the Willamette River.  \n\nPl
 ease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The even
 t will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocol
 ate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed fo
 r the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Loo
 king to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of 
 more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/g
 roup-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals
  or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny
  or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more informat
 ion. We look forward to seeing you out there!
