DESCRIPTION:<p><b>======</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event 
 is <u>full and closed</u>. </b>Please consider any of our events that still
  need planting support.  We hope to plant with you soon!</p><p><b>======</b
 ></p><p><b>Thank you for signing-up to plant hundreds of native trees and s
 hrubs at our annual North Clackamas Watershed Council partnership event! </
 b><span>Friends of Trees is pleased to be working alongside the watershed c
 ouncil at this site along the Mt. Scott Creek Trail\, and can't wait to see
  you at this fun event planting hundreds of native trees and shrubs.</span>
 <br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting cr
 ew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting
  guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all
  you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or 
 boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><span> We reque
 st that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and 
 older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a </span><a href=
 "http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a>
 <span> signed by their parent/guardian.</span><br></p><p><b>Plant giveaway<
 /b>: <span>This event is happening in tandem with a FOT free native tree an
 d shrub giveaway at Spring Mountain (made possible by funding from the Arbo
 r Day Foundation) from 10:00am-12:30pm. Volunteers are eligible to receive 
 up to 4 native trees and/or shrubs (per household). This giveaway is focuse
 d on volunteers and Clackamas County residents\, though all are welcome. Tr
 ees and shrubs will be available on a first-come\, first-served basis. Volu
 nteers that arrive early (between 8:30-8:45am) can request that we hold pla
 nts for them to pick up post-planting event.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </
 b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">
 <u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our t
 eam is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friends
 oftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u>
 </u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /
 ><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with <span>Clackamas Water Envi
 ronment Services and North Clackamas Watershed Council.</span></p>
