DESCRIPTION:<b>***Due to popular interest\, this planting is now closed to 
 further groups.***</b> RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 
 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nJoin Friends of Trees just outside
  of Woodhaven Park this season in partnership with Tualatin Riverkeepers\, 
 the City of Sherwood\, and Clean Water Services. This planting is part of t
 he Tree For All campaign which has planted over three million native plants
  in the Tualatin River Watershed in the past decade! Clean Water Services\,
  Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city part
 ners\, and private landowners will be working together this season to conti
 nue the success of this program.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be regis
 tered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We p
 rovide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tool
 s and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, cl
 osed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\nDo not hesitate to contact Je
 nny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more infor
 mation. \n\nWe look forward to planting together soon!
