DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>=============<u></u><br><br><u></u><b>Due to 
 popular interest this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider 
 joining another open event -- thank you for your consideration!<br><u></u><
 br>=============<br><u></u><br>Help plant hundreds of native shrubs and wil
 dflowers near the headwaters of Wilkes Creek! Please note: this event's sta
 rt time is one hour later than most of our events.<br><u></u><p>Please arri
 ve by <u>9:45am</u> to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plantin
 g starts at <u>10:00am</u>. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidan
 ce -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy 
 shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\
 ;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\
 ; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&
 nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form
 </a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b>What about Cov
 id-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one prior
 ity at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are
  fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as
  children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b
 >\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, 
 respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bri
 ng your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, 
 and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of thi
 s event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer
 -faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for mo
 re details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\
 ;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.o
 rg/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also h
 appy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<
 a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.or
 g</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr><b
 r></b>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with Portland OIC and Portland
  Parks &amp\; Recreation with support from the East Multnomah Soil &amp\; W
 ater Conservation District and Portland Clean Energy Fund to help restore t
 his important natural area.<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow 
 the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Author
 ity. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel
  them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u></html-bl
 ob>
