CREATED:20220826T185804Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Your he
 lp is needed to help plant at Wapato Lake National Wildlife Refuge\, one of
  the nation's newest refuges!</b> This site consists of 817 acres within a 
 5\,000 acre network of near-contiguous publicly-owned natural areas connect
 ing wetlands\, floodplains\, and waterways\, is of critical importance to t
 he health of water\, wildlife and people across the Portland metro area.&nb
 sp\;<u></u><br><br><u></u><u></u>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be 
 assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\
 , tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/te
 a/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather we
 aring sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><u></u><u></u><b
 r><u></u>*Expect a <u>15-25 minute walk</u> from parking area to the planti
 ng site.*<br><br><b>How do I register?</b> Register by filling out this<a h
 ref="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000P0ZJr&tfa_2189=Wapat
 o%20Lake%20planting\,%20Gaston&tfa_31=a0V5G00000UaYJB&tfa_45=Tree%20Planter
 \,%20%20at%20October%2022\,%202022%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_2190=2022-10-22&tfa
 _49=4.25&tfa_886=Clean%20Water%20Services&tfa_51=offsite"> <b>quick form</b
 ></a>. Group and individuals welcome!<br><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We r
 equest that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; You
 th 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\
