DESCRIPTION:<br>============<br><br>Due to popular interest\, this event is
  now full and closed to further volunteers -- thank you for your support! P
 lease consider our next event on May 18th...<br><br>============<br><br><br
 >Your help is needed to remove tree and ground ivy to preserve the tree can
 opy within Tranquil Park -- thank you for supporting greater access to park
 s and natural areas while caring for trees!&nbsp\; Our Tree Care events hel
 p to ensure the highest level of plant survival through our dry summer mont
 hs. <br><br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast
  treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. Tree Care activities start pro
 mptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, but due to the 
 hands-on nature of invasive removal\, we highly recommend wearing lightweig
 ht\, <u>long-sleeve shirts and long pants</u> you don't mind getting dirty.
  Sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of <i>any </i>kind\, please!) â and be
  ready to have fun!<br><br><b><u>Under age 18?</u></b> A signed <b><a href=
 "http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target
 ="_blank">youth waiver</a></b> is required for you to volunteer. We ask tha
 t youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Please con
 tact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunte
 er@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if 
 you have questions or need any further information. We look forward to seei
 ng you out there!
