DESCRIPTION:===============<u></u>==<br><br><b>This event is canceled.&nbsp
 \;</b>&nbsp\;Based on recent recommendations from public health officials\,
  we’re respecting their advice to create a pause in social gatherings and n
 ot voluntarily bringing a group of people together.&nbsp\; We sincerely apo
 logize for this inconvenience and hope to reunite with you under safer cond
 itions soon!<br><br><br>==========<u></u>=======&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><b>What a
 bout Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number o
 ne priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our ev
 ents bring and wear a fabric face mask\, respect 6' or more of distance fro
 m others not in their own household\,bringing your own water bottle and any
  other snacks or beverages you will need\,&nbsp\;and follow a few other pro
 tocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Asked-Questions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\;<br>
 <br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer
  with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their o
 wn and will need to include their parent/guardian's contact information whe
 n they register online.<br><br>Nearly 20 years ago Friends of Trees and the
  City of Wilsonville planted a section of field near the Willamette River. 
 Now that area has the start of a healthy forest growing and is ready for us
  to add the understory plants and help this patch of habitat an important b
 oost.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out 
 our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer 
 FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You ca
 n reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friend
 softrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward
  to seeing you out there!&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continue
 s to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon H
 ealth Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we
  will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
