DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Your help is needed to help plant at Wapato Lake National
  Wildlife Refuge\, one of the nation's newest refuges! </b>This site consis
 ts of 817 acres within a 5\,000 acre network of near-contiguous publicly-ow
 ned natural areas connecting wetlands\, floodplains\, and waterways\, is of
  critical importance to the health of water\, wildlife and people across th
 e Portland metro area. Please join for a fun morning planting in the wetlan
 ds!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting cre
 w. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting 
 guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all 
 you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or b
 oots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Pre-regist
 ration has closed\, but there's still room at this event! Please simply sho
 w-up at 8:45am\, and sign-in when you arrive at the welcome table.</p><p><b
 >Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a pare
 nt/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need t
 o hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_
 blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p>
 <p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></
 b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a 
 href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting toget
 her soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event in partnership with Clean Water Ser
 vices\, USFWS\, and Friends of Tualatin River National Wildlife Refuge Comp
 lex.<br></p>
