DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Your help is n
 eeded to plant native trees and shrubs at this event! </b>This planting is 
 at beautiful Jackson Bottom Wetlands Preserve\, an amazing and unique wildl
 ife preserve. Jackson Bottom is a 635-acre wetland complex on the Tualatin 
 River that is designated as an Important Bird Area for both migrating and n
 on-migratory species. Thank you for considering signing-up -- your particip
 ation is crucial for this project's success!<u></u><br><br><u></u>Please ar
 rive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting sta
 rts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well 
 as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is s
 how up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready
  to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register?</b> Register by filling out <a h
 ref="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000P0ZJp&tfa_2189=Jacks
