DESCRIPTION:<p><b>======</b></p><p><b>This event is full and closed.</b>  P
 lease consider another open planting - we hope to work with yu soon!</p><p>
 <b>======</b></p><p><b>Your help is needed to plant hundreds of native tree
 s and shrubs at the unique Gateway Green Park in NE Portland! </b><span>Hel
 p enhance the natural area in this unique mountain-biking oasis situated in
  between I-84 and I-205. This event *would not be possible* without communi
 ty support - thanks for considering signing-up!</span><br></p><p><em>This p
 ark is only accessible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. There is an approximat
 ely 10 - 15 minute walk from the **SW corner** of the Fred Meyer parking lo
 t (by the garden center across from The Oregon Clinic) down the multi-use p
 ath to our planting site\, look for our signs. Volunteers are encouraged to
  bike to the planting or take public transportation to the transit center a
 nd walk from there.</em></p><p>*Please note this event starts 1 hour later 
 than most of our plantings. <u>Please arrive by 9:45am</u> to sign-in and b
 e assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 10:00am. We provide glov
 es\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee
 /tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather
  wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<b><br></b></p><p
 ><b>Under age 18?</b><span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer wi
 th a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and wi
 ll need to hand us a </span><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"
 ><u><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></u></a><span> signed by their parent/gu
 ardian.</span><br></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FA
 Q webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assis
 t!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><
 u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a> We loo
 k forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our even
 t sponsors <a href="https://www.nba.com/blazers/threesfortrees"><u><u>Portl
 and Trail Blazers &amp\; Daimler Truck North America</u></u></a>\, <a href=
 "https://laughingplanet.com/">Laughing Planet</a>\, and <a href="https://ww
 w.acmsnw.com/">ACMS NW</a>.</p><p>===</p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This ev
 ent is in partnership with Friends of Gateway Green\, Portland Parks and Re
 creation\, and Portland OIC.<br></p>
