DESCRIPTION:We will be planting some additional Oregon White Oaks and mulch
 ing native trees and shrubs that were planted this past winter to prepare t
 hem for survival during the drier and warmer summer months.  Please join us
 !\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. T
 he event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot
  chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dre
 ssed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun! \n
 \n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for gr
 oups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/vo
 lunteer/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for gr
 oups of 4 or less.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if yo
 u have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing yo
 u out there!\n\n<i>Friends of Trees is excited to be planting at the Sandy 
 River Delta again! We are partnering with the Sandy River Basin Watershed C
 ouncil and Friends of the Sandy River Delta with support from East Multnoma
 h Soil & Water Conservation District\, the US Forest Service\, PGE's Habita
 t Fund\, and the Jubitz Foundation.</i>\n\n\n<i>This event is generously sp
 onsored by <b>Portland General Electric</b>.</I>\n\n
