DESCRIPTION:Despite some winter weather this week\, this planting is contin
 uing as planned -- please join us!<br><br>Join Friends of Trees at Woodhave
 n City Park this season in partnership with Tualatin Riverkeepers\, the Cit
 y of Sherwood\, and Clean Water Services. This planting is part of Tree For
  All\, a partnership which has planted more than eight million native plant
 s in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friend
 s of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, 
 and private landowners will be working together this season to continue the
  success of this program.<br><br>**Please note: this event is *not* at Wood
 haven Park\, but at our planting site a couple blocks North of the park.&nb
 sp\; Please follow our signs as you get close!<br><br>Please arrive around 
 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start prompt
 ly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as wel
 l as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and w
 earing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun!<br><br><b>Looki
 ng to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of mo
 re than 5 people - click <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2
 Ffriendsoftrees.org%2Fvolunteering%2Fgroup-registration&amp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=
 1519067050571000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNGJUwJx5tLcpxJWs14ZDxV04FhtKw" target="_blan
 k">HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4
  or fewer -- you can simply show up!<br><br>Are you under age 18 and planti
 ng without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href="https://www.google.com/
 url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.friendsoftrees.org%2Fimages%2Fstories%2Fpdf%2FYouth_
 Waiver_2015.pdf&amp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=1519067050571000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNErFxKWEd
 Gzs_uzqaX-CZuWfO3rMQ" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you 
 to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanied 
 by an adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you 
 have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you 
 out in Sherwood!<br><br><i>Accessible on Bus Line 94.  For more directions\
 , visit <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Ftrimet.org%2F&a
 mp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=1519067050571000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNGixjquP5-f5LFV5WNaRHtWw9k
