DESCRIPTION:===========<br>This training is <b><u>full and closed</u></b>. 
 Please consider the next Green Space training for the Crew Leader position 
 on Sat\, Jan 27th!<br>===========<br><br><a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Planting C</a><a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">rew Leaders</a> 
 are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading small 
 group at our community planting events. Friends of Trees can not run these 
 events without the support of this valued position!  <span>After your train
 ing\, we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Oct-No
 v (select for events that fit your schedule!).    </span><br><br><i>*Please
  note that we welcome Crew Leaders age 16 and older\, and this is an all-ag
 es venue.</i><br><br><u>This is the hands-on training for new Crew Leaders 
 in the Green Space program.  Please note: trainees will need to have comple
 ted the online training before they attend this hands-on session</u>.  The 
 online session will be available for two weeks prior for you to complete fr
 om home.<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn 
 about tree identification\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and mee
 t the staff you'll be working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the
  <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader
 /">Planting Crew Leader webpage</a> or contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@f
 riendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>
