DESCRIPTION:Friends of Trees is working with Clean Water Services to restor
 e the Portland Community College floodplain adjacent to the school's campus
 . This stretch of Rock Creek is rich with wildlife and the native trees and
  shrubs that we will be planting will help further improve their habitat an
 d buffer the creek from nearby new housing construction. This planting is p
 art of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than eight milli
 on native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Se
 rvices\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, c
 ity partners\, and private landowners will be working together this season 
 to continue the success of this program.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to 
 be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9
 :00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gl
 oves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing 
 sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volu
 nteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 
 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registr
 ation>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups o
 f 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nAre you under age 18 and plantin
 g without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees
 .org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required 
 for you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are acco
 mpanied by an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if 
 you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing 
 you at our event!
