 enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planti
 ng starts at 9:00am. <span><span><b>Please park along SE Alta Vista Dr</b> 
 being careful not to block driveways. Once you have parked\, look for the F
 riends of Trees signs to guide you as you arrive! </span></span>We provide 
 gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dre
 ssed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have f
 un! <br><br><br><b>Pre-Registration for this event is now closed</b>\, but 
 we still have plenty of space left! Feel free to simply show up tomorrow at
  8:45 am--we would love to work with you!<br><br><b><u>Under age 18?</u></b
 > A signed youth waiver is required for youth to volunteer: <b><a href="htt
 p://www.friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">www.friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver<
 /a></b> We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.
 <br><br>This event is in partnership with North Clackamas Urban Watersheds 
 Council and the Happy Valley Heights HOA and possible with the support of C
 lackamas County Water Environment Services.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, P
 ablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftr
