 ed for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not req
 uired for groups of 4 or less.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 59
 5-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward 
 to seeing you out there!\n\n<i>Come share your love of planting trees with 
 Tigard Mayor Cook\, Friends of Trees\, the City of Tigard and Clean Water S
 ervices at this Valentine's Day planting. This planting is part of the Tree
  For All campaign which strives to plant one million native trees and shrub
 s during the 2014-2015 planting season within the Tualatin River Watershed!
  Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other 
 non-profits\, City partners\, and private landowners will all be working to
 gether to make this happen!</i>
