DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u>full and close
 d</u></b>. Please consider our Gresham planting (2.5 miles from this site) 
 this same day in the afternoon.  We hope to plant with you soon!<br></p><p>
 =====================================================</p><p>Wilkes Creek is
  one of the last remaining surface creeks providing clean\, cold water dire
 ctly to the Columbia Slough\, and we need your help to continue restoring i
 t! Come to this event where we'll be planting hundreds of native shrubs and
  wildflowers to restore and protect the Columbia Slough watershed!<br></p><
 p>Please arrive by 9:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The p
 lanting starts at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, as we
 ll as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate. We ask that all 
 volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/boots you don't mind g
 etting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href=
 "http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u>youth waiver 
 form</u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Question
 s?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></a></u></b>
 .  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a hr
 ef="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><b><u>volunteer
 @friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to pla
 nting together soon!<br></p><b><hr /></b><p>This event made possible throug
 h a grant from the USDA Forest Service. This institution is an equal opport
 unity provider.<br></p>
