DESCRIPTION:We are very excited to continue reforesting the transportation 
 corridor that runs from the Columbia River in the North to the City of Glad
 stone in the south. Metro\, ODOT\, BES\, and the Port of Portland are partn
 ering with Friends of Trees to increase livability\, habitat and air qualit
 y along the I-205 corridor. Come celebrate the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther 
 King Jr. by volunteering on this special day.  Friends of Trees will provid
 e morning refreshments\, gloves\, tools\, and all necessary guidance. This 
 planting is generously sponsored by REI. Please wear sturdy shoes and dress
  for the weather. Please contact Andy Meeks at AndyM@FriendsofTrees.org or 
 503-282-8846 x24 for more information.
