DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to plant native trees and shrubs near the c
 onfluence of Rock Creek and the Clackamas River. Friends of Trees is partne
 ring with the Clackamas River Basin Council and the Windswept Waters HOA to
  enhance this important natural area in Clackamas County. <br><br>Please ar
 rive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\
 , or hot chocolate. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide glov
 es\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for th
 e weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â and be ready to have fun! <
 br><br><b>How do I register?</b>&nbsp\;Online registration closes 24 hours 
 before the event begins.&nbsp\; You're welcome to simply show up though!&nb
 sp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A signed <b><a href="http://friendsoftrees
 .org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver
 </a></b> is required for you to volunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and y
 ounger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, a
 nd Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"
  target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or 
 need any further information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
