CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:<b>**Due to popular interest\, this event is now full and close
 d to further volunteer groups.</b> Individuals and small groups of 4 or few
 er are welcome to simply show up!**\n\nJoin us on this special Monday plant
 ing to help celebrate the Martin Luther King Jr. Day of Service!\n\nFriends
  of Trees is excited to continue our partnership this season with the City 
 of Tualatin and Clean Water Services. This planting is part of Tree For All
 \, a partnership which has planted more than eight million native plants in
  the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of
  Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and 
 private landowners will be working together this season to continue the suc
 cess of this program.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and a
 ssigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide b
 reakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and gu
 idance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe
  shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\nAre you under age 18 and planting wit
 hout your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/
 images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required for y
 ou to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompani
 ed by an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you h
 ave any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you a
 t Ibach Park! \n\n<i>Accessible on Bus Line 96.  For more directions\, visi
 t <a href=https://trimet.org/>https://trimet.org/</a>.</i>
