 r>Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that wer
 e planted this past winter at this special gem of a site in inner NE Portla
 nd! We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbs
 p\;<u>Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is phys
 ically-demanding work</u>&nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&
 nbsp\; Our Tree Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant survi
 val through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><br><b>Please arrive by 9:4
 5am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\, Tree Care activities start promptly 
 at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to d
 o is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no 
 sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>What abo
 ut Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one
  priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our even
