DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><b>==========</b></html-blob><br><html-blob><b><br><
 /b></html-blob><br><html-blob><b><u>Due to popular interest\, this event is
  full and closed</u>.&nbsp\;</b> Please consider any of our other open even
 ts -- thank you for your support!</html-blob><br><html-blob><b><br></b></ht
 ml-blob><br><html-blob><br><b>==========</b></html-blob><br><html-blob><br>
 </html-blob><br><html-blob><u></u><b>Join Friends of Trees\, Columbia Sloug
 h Watershed Council\, and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation in planting at t
 his unique property in NE Portland!</b> We'll be planting hundreds of nativ
 e shrubs and trees along Johnson Lake and the adjacent slough channel. Than
 k you for considering signing up to help with this important initiative!<u>
 </u><br><br><u></u>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a pla
 nting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and 
 planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolat
 e -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy s
 hoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<u></u><br><p><b>What about Covid-
 19?</b><span>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;</span><u>require</u><span>&nbsp\;that all peo
 ple at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to 
 someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\;
  We&nbsp\;</span><u>recommend&nbsp\;</u><span>everyone is fully-vaccinated\
 , bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6
 ’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;</span><b><u><a href="https://
 friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Aske
 d Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b><span>&nbsp\;for more de
 tails.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</span><br></p><p><b>Questions?
 &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u
 ></u></u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You 
 can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friend
 softrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></
 u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr><
 /b><p>This event is in partnership with Portland Parks and Recreation\, Col
 umbia Slough Watershed Council and the Clean Air Canopy coalition.&nbsp\;&n
 bsp\;</p><p>This planting is part of an effort to remedy toxic air pollutio
 n from a nearby glass plant that was fined by Oregon's DEQ. The trees plant
 ed at this event will bring long-term human and environmental health benefi
 ts to the area. Clean Air Canopy partner groups include Verde\, Columbia Sl
 ough Watershed Council Cully Association of Neighbors\, Cully Air Action Te
 am\, and Friends of Trees.<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u
 ></html-blob>
