 8th******</b></p><p>Due to snow\, Friends of Trees has made the difficult d
 ecision to <b><u>reschedule our Jackson School Natural Area planting.</u></
 b> Temperatures will remain mostly below freezing Thurs-Sat\, and we're con
 cerned about road conditions as well as comfort planting in 25* weather.  W
 ithout snow substantially melting (which is unlikely)\, it will also be dif
 ficult to see the holes for planting the trees.  We're very sorry for this 
 change in plan!</p><p><b>If you are able\, please <a href="https://www.tfaf
 orms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0T5G00000P0u6T&tfa_2189=Jackson%20School%20Natural
 %20Area%20planting\,%20Hillsboro&tfa_31=a0V5G00000UajaR&tfa_45=Tree%20Plant
 er\,%20%20at%20March%2018\,%202023%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_2190=2023-03-18&tfa
 _49=4.15&tfa_886=Clean%20Water%20Services&tfa_51=offsite"><u>sign up here</
 u></a> for the rescheduled event on Sat\, March 18th </b>or let our volunte
 er team know and they can transfer your registration: <a href="mailto:volun
 teer@friendsoftrees.org"><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></a>. We apprec
 iate the support of our community!</p><br><b>========</b><br><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><b>Friends of Trees is working with Clean Water Services and 
 the Jackson School HOA to restore this natural area to a diverse and health
 y forest. And we need help! </b> The focus of this event will be pulling iv
 y and planting of hundreds of trees and shrubs -- and this is only possible
  with community support of volunteer like you!<br><br><u></u>Please arrive 
 by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts a
 t 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as br
 eakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show u
 p dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to h
 ave fun!<b><br></b><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and und
 er volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on t
 heir own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.or
 g/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their paren
 t/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We <u>require</u> that all pe
 ople at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to
  someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.  We <
 u>recommend </u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a face mask w
 hen working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical distance. Please
  see our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> for more details.
         </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https
 ://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>V
 olunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u
 ></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel and Jenny 
 at <b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> We look forward to planting together soon!</p
 ><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://portlandgeneral.
 com/"><u><u>PGE</u></u></a>.<br>===<br></p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in
  partnership with Clean Water Services and the City of Hillsboro\, and<u></
 u> is part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than ten 
 million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Wat
 er Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profit
 s\, city partners\, and private landowners will be working together this se
 ason to continue the success of this program.</p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u>
