DESCRIPTION:<p><b>===============</b></p><p><b>Registration is now FULL &am
 p\; CLOSED. Please consider registering for any open event - we hope to pla
 nt with you soon!</b></p><p><b>===============</b></p><p><span>Join Friends
  of Trees and Clean Water Services to plant hundreds of native trees and sh
 rubs along Summer Creek in Beaverton. Thanks for considering signing-up to 
 green this special site!</span></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in an
 d be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gl
 oves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coff
 ee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weath
 er wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>U
 nder age 18?</b><span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a 
 parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will ne
 ed to hand us a </span><b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver
 " target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b><span> signed by their parent/gua
 rdian.</span></p><p><span><b>Transit: </b></span><span>Bus Line 62.</span><
 /p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>. 
  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href
 ="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!<
 /p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https://portlandgener
 al.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u></a>
  &amp\; <a href="https://www.hamptonlumber.com/" target="_blank"><u>Hampton
