 ent is now full and closed</b></u>.&nbsp\; Please consider signing-up for a
 ny of our other open events!<br><br>==================<br><br>Join Friends 
 of Trees as we mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that were planted 
 this past winter in celebration of Earth Week! We may also take out some we
 edy introduced plants\, if time allows. Our Tree Care events help to ensure
  the highest level of plant survival through our dry summer months.&nbsp\;<
 br><br>Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew.
  The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and h
 ot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come d
 ressed for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes (no sandals of any kind\, please
 !)\, and get ready to have fun!<br><b><u></u></b><br><b><u>Under age 18?</u
 ></b> A signed <b><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/You
 th_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a></b> is required for yo
 u to volunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by a
 n adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, or Carey at (503) 595-0213 /
