CREATED:20220203T000628Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><br>====<br><br>Due to popular interest this event i
 s now&nbsp\;<u><b>full and closed</b></u>.&nbsp\; We hope to work with you 
 next planting/tree care season -- events start again in Oct!<br><br>====<u>
 </u><br><u></u><u></u><b>Celebrate Earth Day with Friends of Trees!</b> The
  goal of this event is to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that we
 re recently planted at this well-loved Tualatin park. We may also take out 
 some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>Note: there will be
  no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u>
 &nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tree Care even
 ts help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry s
 ummer months ahead.<br><br><b>Please arrive by 8:45am</b>&nbsp\;to find our
  tent and sign-in\, Tree Care activities start promptly at 9:00am. We provi
 de gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed
  for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\
 , please!) and be ready to have fun!<p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We reques
 t that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16
  and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&n
 bsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbs
 p\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends
  of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccina
 ted (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children youn
 ger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event int
 roductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own ho
 usehold\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you
  will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two
  weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.
 org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>
 &nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Que
 stions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our t
 eam is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jen
 ny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to working together soon!<br><
 /p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with and supported by the Cit
 y of Tualatin and Clean Water Services.</p><p><i>Friends of Trees continues
  to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon He
 alth Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we 
 will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i></p><
 u></u><u></u></html-blob>
