DESCRIPTION:Friends of Trees is working with Clean Water Services to restor
 e the Churchill Forest natural area to a diverse and healthy riparian fores
 t and ephemeral wetland. This planting project is situated in the headwater
 s of Summer Creek and will help to protect the uppermost section of the wat
 ershed by planting a wide variety of native trees and shrubs. \n\nPlease ar
 rive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting wi
 ll start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/
 coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for th
 e weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun!\
 n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for g
 roups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for in
 dividuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nAre you und
 er age 18 and planting without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http
 ://www.friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth wa
 iver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years
  and younger are accompanied by an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo 
 at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. \n\nW
 e look forward to seeing you at the planting!
