DESCRIPTION:<b>Due to unexpected icy site and road conditions lingering in 
 the Columbia Gorge\, this planting is now CANCELLED.  Please consider our G
 resham planting if you'd like to plant trees today!</b>\n\nFriends of Trees
  is partnering with the Sandy River Basin Watershed Council and Friends of 
 the Sandy River Delta with support from the US Forest Service\, Daimler\, t
 he Portland Trail Blazers\, PGE's Habitat Fund\, Ash Creek Forestry Managem
 ent\, and the Jubitz Foundation to continue native seedling plantings at th
 e Sandy River Delta.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and as
 signed to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide br
 eakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and gui
 dance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get
  ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are ki
 ndly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://frie
 ndsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are
  not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may simply sho
 w up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any qu
 estions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!\
 n\n<b>Thank you to the PORTLAND TRAIL BLAZERS\, DAIMLER TRUCKS NA\, and THE
  PORT OF PORTLAND for generously sponsoring this planting event.<b>\n\n
