DESCRIPTION:<b>UPDATE: Due to snow accumulation and freezing site condition
 s\, this planting is postponed until further notice.</b> We apologize for a
 ny inconvenience and thank you for your flexibility!\n\n==\n\nFriends of Tr
 ees is working in partnership with the Tualatin River Watershed Council and
  Clean Water Services to help restore the Bonita natural area to a diverse 
 and healthy riparian forest ecosystem. This planting is part of the Tree Fo
 r All campaign which has planted over three million native plants in the Tu
 alatin River Watershed in the past decade! Clean Water Services\, Friends o
 f Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and
  private landowners will be working together this season to continue the su
 ccess of this program.\n\nThis site is in Bonita Townhomes. The closest add
 ress to our planting site is 20 SW Weaver Way\, Tigard\, OR 97224.\n\nPleas
 e arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The plantin
 g will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocol
 ate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed fo
 r the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have f
 un!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested f
 or groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/v
 olunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required fo
 r individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may simply show up!\n\nPlease 
 contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need 
 more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
