DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><p><b>Friends of Trees n
 eeds help to restore the Churchill Forest Natural Area to a diverse and hea
 lthy riparian forest and wetland - join this event to plant hundreds of nat
 ive trees and shrubs!</b> This planting project is situated at the headwate
 rs of Summer Creek and will help to protect the uppermost section of the wa
 tershed by planting a wide variety of native trees and shrubs. Thank you fo
 r considering signing-up -- your participation is crucial for this project'
 s success!<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a p
 lanting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, an
 d planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocol
 ate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy
  shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register? </
 b>Register by filling out <b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_
 26=a0T5G00000P0ZJo&tfa_2189=Churchill%20Forest%20Natural%20Area%20planting\
 ,%20Beaverton&tfa_31=a0V5G00000UaYJ3&tfa_45=Tree%20Planter\,%20%20at%20Octo
 ber%208\,%202022%20at%208:45%20am&tfa_2190=2022-10-08&tfa_49=4.25&tfa_886=C
 lean%20Water%20Services&tfa_51=offsite">this quick form</a></b>.&nbsp\; Gro
 up and individuals welcome!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request tha
 t youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and 
 older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a 
 href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></u></b>&
 nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b> We
  <u>require</u> that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unw
 ell or have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within
  3 days of the event.&nbsp\; We <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-va
 ccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and 
 respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions w
 ebpage</a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&n
 bsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage<
 /a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach 
 Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.o
 rg">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to plant
 ing together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This planting is in partnership with Cl
 ean Water Services and part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has plant
 ed more than ten million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed sinc
 e 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\,
  other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners will be working
  together this season to continue the success of this program.<br></p><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
