 .&nbsp\; Thank you very much for your interest\, we hope to work with you a
 t another event that fits into your schedule!<br><br>*****************<br>J
 oin us in partnership with North Clackamas Urban Watersheds Council to plan
 t native trees and shrubs near the headwaters of Mount Scott Creek! This pl
 anting is possible with the support of Clackamas County Water Environment S
 ervices. Hundreds of native trees and shrubs are ready to be planted at thi
 s site -- and your help is much appreciated to ensure they can be planted i
 n their new home! <br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some
  breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts 
 promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you n
 eed to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or bo
 ots â and be ready to have fun!&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A sign
 ed <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.
 pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We 
 ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Ple
 ase contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:
 volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org<
 /a> if you have questions or need any further information. We look forward 
 to seeing you out there!<br><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a 
 href="https://www.portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank">PGE</a>.<br>===&nbs
 p\;&nbsp\;
