DESCRIPTION:Join us as we mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that we
 re planted this past winter! Our Tree Care events help to ensure the highes
 t level of plant survival through our dry summer months.<b><br><br>Looking 
 to volunteer as a group?</b>&nbsp\;RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of
  more than 5 people - click&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=htt
 p%3A%2F%2Ffriendsoftrees.org%2Fvolunteering%2Fgroup-registration&amp\;sa=D&
 amp\;ust=1524419014795000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNFL7hJa7LYo5DaS1F-q8BvT7VOS5Q" targ
 et="_blank">HERE</a>&nbsp\;to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals
  or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may simply show up!<br><br>Please arrive ar
 ound 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start p
 romptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, a
 s well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather\
 , wear sturdy shoes\, and get ready to have fun!<br><br>This event is in pa
 rtnership with the City of Lake Oswego.<br><br>Are you under age 18 and pla
 nting without your parent/guardian? A signed&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.goo
