DESCRIPTION:<b>UPDATE: Due to forecasted inclement weather and freezing sit
 e conditions\, this planting is postponed until further notice. We apologiz
 e for any inconvenience and thank you for your flexibility!</b>\n\n==\n\nKi
 ck off the new year right by planting native trees and shrubs along Chastai
 n Creek! This planting is in partnership with Johnson Creek Watershed Counc
 il\, East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation District\, Metro\, and the Ci
 ty of Gresham.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned
  to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast s
 nacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Pl
 ease come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and
  get ready to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs a
 re kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVP
 s are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you may simpl
 y show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have a
 ny questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out th
 ere!
