DESCRIPTION:<p>Help needed to plant hundreds of native plants at the King's
  Bend natural area site! Join Friends of Trees\, Clean Water Services\, Met
 ro\, and the City of Cornelius as we restore this important area. This plan
 ting is part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than te
 n million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005. </p><p>
 Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The pla
 nting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\,
  as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need t
 o do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and
  be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Onlin<u></u><u><
 /u>e registration has closed at this time\, but there is still room at this
  event\, please simply <u>show up at 8:45am</u> and sign-in when you arrive
 . Parking is a 10 minute walk from planting site\, please plan accordingly.
  </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer w
 ith a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and w
 ill need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"
  target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver 
 form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b
 > signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check ou
 t our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_bl
 ank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our 
 team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mai
 lto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!</p><hr /><p><b></b></p><p>This event is in pa
 rtnership with Clean Water Services.</p>
