DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><b><br><hr><p></p><a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Planting C</a><a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">rew Leaders</a><
 /b>&nbsp\;are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and lead
 ing small group at Friends of Trees community planting events. We can not r
 un these events without the support of this valued position! This training 
 is for the Green Space program where you'll plant small-stock (gallon conta
 iner or smaller) native trees and shrubs in an ecological-rest<u></u>oratio
 n style in parks and natural areas.<br><br><b><a href="https://friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Learn more and register her
 e</a></b>&nbsp\;for this important position. Space limited.<br><b><p></p></
 b><ul><li><b><u>A note on planting location and personal transportation</u>
 :<u></u></b>&nbsp\;You will be eligible to Crew Lead at plantings in cities
  across Washington County\, and a handful of sites in Multnomah and Clackam
 as Counties (check out the green events here on the online calendar for mor
 e details). Personal transportation is recommended-- we do use a carpooling
  tool but cannot guarantee that carpools will be available due to differing
  comfort levels of other FOT volunteers.</li></ul><ul><li><b><u>What about 
 Covid-19?</u></b>&nbsp\; Friends of Trees&nbsp\;<u>requires</u> that all pe
 ople at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to
  someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\
 ; We <u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>every<u></u>one is fully-vaccinate<u></u>d\, br
 ing and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of
  physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftr
 ees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u>
 </a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.</li></ul><b><p></p><hr><p></p></b>Ple<
 u></u>a<u></u>se contact Jenny or Gabriel if you need more information or h
 ave questions:&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volu<u><
 /u>nteer@frien<u></u>dsof<u></u>trees.org</a>. We look forward to working w
 ith you this planting season!</html-blob>
