 n Water Services. We will be primarily focusing on the removal of invasive 
 English Ivy from trees within Brown's Ferry Park and depending on the weath
 er\, we may also be planting a limited number of native trees and shrubs. C
 ome give a tree a hug at this community park located along the banks of the
  Tualatin River. \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assig
 ned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfas
 t snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance.
  Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready
  to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly 
 requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are 
 not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show
  up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any que
 stions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
