DESCRIPTION:<p><span>Friends of Trees\, in partnership with the City of Tua
 latin and Clean Water Services\, is excited to be providing an opportunity 
 for the community to get outside and give back in a safe\, physically-dista
 nced way. Throughout this scheduled week\, pre-registered volunteers will b
 e helping mulch recently-planted native trees\, shrubs\, and plants at Brow
 n’s Ferry Park! Mulching is an important step to ensure the survival of the
 se new friends during the tough summer conditions. </span><span>To reduce t
 he risks of spreading COVID-19 among volunteers and staff\, there are a num
 ber of adjustments that have been made. Please read all of the details belo
 w before signing up for a shift. </span><span>While we love to have fun at 
 our events\, we take our volunteer and staff safety very seriously. Thank y
 ou for your understanding and patience as we pilot this revised program to 
 continue this work under the limiting conditions we have.</span></p><ul><li
 ><p><span>We are recruiting for multiple volunteer shifts between Saturday\
 , 8/15 through Friday\, 8/21.</span></p></li><li><p><b><u>Pre-registration 
 is required</u>.</b> In order to volunteer\, you must reserve your spot on 
 a shift and <b><span>show up at that time.</span></b></p></li><li><p><span>
 <b>Only one individual (or household) is allowed per volunteer shift.</b> <
 /span><span>To minimize exposure between multiple households\, we are limit
 ing one household per volunteer shift.</span></p><ul><li><p><span>When we s
 ay household\, this could be with housemates or family members that share t
 he same home. You can also volunteer solo!</span></p></li><li><p><span>No s
 taff member will be present. For any youth age 16 or older hoping to volunt
 eer on their own\, a contact number of a legal guardian will be required so
  that we can confirm details and permission via phone. If you are an adult 
 signing up your child\, there are instructions in the waiver/registration f
 orm for you to register them.</span></p></li></ul></li><li><p><span><b>Ever
 y volunteer from the household must sign a waiver prior to their shift</b>:
  </span><span>In addition to your registration and waiver\, each member of 
 your household will need to have a signed waiver before volunteering for th
 e designated shift.&nbsp\; Please ask us if have any questions with registe
 ring online.</span></p></li><li><p><span>By signing up\, you also agree to 
 </span><b><span>honor the shift that you have signed up for</span></b><span
 ><b>.</b> For this operation to be successful\, it is important that you ar
 e on site only within your shift time. This is to minimize any overlap betw
 een shifts and ensure that only one household is volunteering at a time. Ag
 ain\, this is for the safety of all.</span></p></li><li><p><b><span>Face co
 verings are required.</span></b></p></li><li><b><span><span><b><span><span>
 <span></span></span>🌳 📝 🌟To view available shifts and sign up\, visit th
 e</span><a href="https://friendsoftrees.secure.force.com/volunteers/"> <spa
 n>Volunteer Page</span></a></b><span>\, select the shift you will commit to
 \, &amp\; complete the waiver per the instructions provided. </span></span>
 </span></b></li></ul><b><span><span><span></span></span></span></b><span><s
 pan><br><span>Thank you so much! We are so happy to be working with you and
  doing our best to make this work. Your cooperation is critical to allowing
  us to host more events throughout the season.</span></span></span><b><span
 ><span><br></span></span></b><span><br></span>
