DESCRIPTION:==========<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u
 >full and closed</u></b>. Please consider any other open planting event -- 
 thank you for your support!<br><br><br>==========<br>Help plant hundreds of
  native trees and shrubs along the Fanno Creek Trail in Beaverton!<p>Please
  arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting 
 starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all 
 you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or b
 oots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We reques
 t that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16
  and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&n
 bsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>
 &nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Fri
 ends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vac
 cinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children 
 younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nb
 sp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6'
  or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your ow
 n water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel
  if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. P
 lease see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>
 Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details
 .&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</
 b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunte
 er-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to as
 sist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="ma
 ilto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&
 nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><br>This
  planting is in partnership with the City of Beaverton and Clean Water Serv
 ices\, and part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than
  ten million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005!&nbsp
 \;<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recomm
 endations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we f
 eel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volu
 nteers who are pre-registered.</i>
