DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=========</b></p><p><b><u>Due to unexpectedly strong wind
  gusts on site\, this event is canceled</u>.  </b>This planting site is und
 er tree canopy\, and the wind is making it unsafe to plant in this particul
 ar area today. We apologize for any inconvenience this causes\, thank you f
 or your support of community safety! </p><p><b>=========</b></p><p><b>Calli
 ng all nature lovers!  Help needed to plant hundreds of native trees and sh
 rubs at the unique Gateway Green Park in East Portland! </b>Join Friends of
  Trees and Portland Parks and Recreation as we enhance the natural area in 
 this unique mountain-biking oasis situated in between I-84 and I-205. </p><
 p><em>This park is only accessible via the I-205 Multi-Use Path. There is a
 n approximately 15 minute walk from the former Kohl's parking lot down the 
 multi-use path to our planting site\, look for our signs. Volunteers are en
 couraged to bike to the planting or take public transportation to the trans
 it center and walk from there.</em></p><p>Please arrive by 9:45am to sign-i
 n and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 10:00am. We provi
 de gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and
  coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the 
 weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>
 Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a paren
 t/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to
  hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guard
 ian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://
 friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mailto:Volun
 teer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look forward to working toge
 ther soon!<br></p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a href="ht
 tps://wyldcanna.com/" target="_blank"><u><u>WYLD</u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p>
 <b><hr /></b><p>This event in partnership with Portland Parks &amp\; Recrea
 tion and Oregon Department of Forestry. <br></p>
