DESCRIPTION:<b><br><hr><p></p></b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" id="ow9436" __is_owner="true">Planting 
 C</a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-le
 ader/">rew Leaders</a>&nbsp\;are trained volunteers who are crucial to plan
 ting trees and leading small group at our community planting events. Friend
 s of Trees can not run these events without the support of this valued posi
 tion! This training is for the Green Space program where you'll plant small
 -stock (gallon container or smaller) native trees and shrubs in an ecologic
 al-restoration style in parks and natural areas.<br><br><b><a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Learn more and
  register here</a></b>&nbsp\;for this important position. Space limited.<br
 ><b><p></p></b><ul><li><b><u>What about Covid-19?</u></b>&nbsp\;We are requ
 iring that all volunteers and staff are fully-vaccinated\, arrive at all ev
 ents wearing a face masks (depending on the event it may be possible to rem
 ove your mask after planting begins)\, and maintain 6' or more of physical 
 space from folks outside of your household. We'll explain more at the train
 ing\, but also feel free to check out our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoft
 rees.org/volunteer-faq/">Covid-19 &amp\; Volunteer FAQ page</a>&nbsp\;for m
 ore details.</li></ul><ul><li><b><u>A note on planting location and persona
 l transportation</u>:</b>&nbsp\;You will be eligible to Crew Lead at planti
 ngs in cities across Washington County\, and a handful of sites in Multnoma
 h and Clackamas Counties. Due to Covid-19\, personal transportation is high
 ly recommended-- we cannot guarantee that carpools will be available due to
  differing comfort levels of other FOT volunteers.</li></ul><b><p></p><hr><
 p></p></b>Ple<u></u>ase contact Jenny or Carey if you need more information
  or have questions:&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">vol
 unteer@frien<u></u>dsoftrees.org</a>. We look forward to working with you t
 his planting season!
