DESCRIPTION:As part of the Rock Creek Partnership with SOLVE and the Clacka
 mas River Basin Council\, Friends of Trees is leading volunteer restoration
  events along the banks of Rock Creek and its tributaries. Rock Creek is a 
 tributary to the Clackamas River and supports numerous species of wildlife\
 , including salmonids. \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and
  assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide
  breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and 
 guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and 
 get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more tha
 n 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/group-re
 gistration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.   Please contact Andy or Jenny a
 t (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. \n\nTh
 is project is supported by Clackamas County Water Environmental Services\, 
 on behalf of Clackamas Service District No. 1.
