DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at the second of four plantings to help r
 evitalize Hall Creek in the heart of Beaverton. These plantings are part of
  a broader creek restoration project being completed by the City to improve
  water quality and beautify the area. The plantings are in partnership with
  the City of Beaverton and Clean Water Services and supported by a Metro vo
 ter-approved Nature in Neighborhoods grant.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am 
 to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9
 :00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gl
 oves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing 
 sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a gro
 up?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click
  <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE
 </a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or few
 er -- you can simply show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595
 -0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward t
 o seeing you out there!
