CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:Thank you for joining us as we remove introduced weedy plants a
 long this natural area near Trillium Primary School! Our Tree Care events h
 elp to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the dry Pacific N
 orthwest summer months and <b>removing competing species </b>ensures that t
 hey have a better chance of thriving in their new homes.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><
 br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and c
 offee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. Tree Care activities start promptly at 9:00
 am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, but due to the hands-on natu
 re of invasive removal\, we highly recommend wearing <u>lightweight\, long-
 sleeve shirts and long pants</u> you don't mind getting dirty. Sturdy close
 -toe shoes or boots (no sandals of <i>any </i>kind\, please!) â and be re
 ady to have fun! Look for our "Friends of Trees" signs as you get close to 
 guide you.<br><br><u><b>How do I register:</b></u>&nbsp\;Registration close
 s the day before the event\, but there is still a little room at this work 
 party -- please simply show up and check-in at our registration table!<br><
 br><b><u>Under age 18? </u></b>A signed youth waiver is required for you to
  volunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an ad
 ult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <
 a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any further information. W
 e look forward to seeing you out there!
