 crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snac
 ks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Pleas
 e come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to ha
 ve fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly reques
 ted for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftr
 ees.org/volunteer/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not requi
 red for groups of 4 or less.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-02
 13 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to s
 eeing you out there!\n\n<i>Friends of Trees is excited to be partnering wit
 h Raindrops to Refuge and the City of Sherwood with support from Clean Wate
 r Services to return to Woodhaven Park this season. This planting is part o
 f the Tree For All campaign which strives to plant one million native trees
  and shrubs during the 2014-2015 planting season within the Tualatin River 
 Watershed. Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteer
 s\, other non-profits\, City partners\, and private landowners will all be 
 working together to make this happen!</i>
