 nique wildlife preserve. Jackson Bottom is a 635-acre wetland complex on th
 e Tualatin River that is designated as an Important Bird Area for both migr
 ating and non-migratory species.<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-
 in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provi
 de gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and
  coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the 
 weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p
 ><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a p
 arent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target
