DESCRIPTION:Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a 
 crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snac
 ks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Pleas
 e come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to ha
 ve fun! \n\n <b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly reque
 sted for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees
 .org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not requi
 red for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nF
 riends of Trees is excited to continue our partnership this season with the
  City of Beaverton and Clean Water Services. This planting is part of the T
 ree For All campaign which has planted over three million native plants in 
 the Tualatin River Watershed in the past decade! Clean Water Services\, Fri
 ends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners
 \, and private landowners will be working together this season to continue 
 the success of this program. \n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595
 -0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward t
 o seeing you out there!
