DESCRIPTION:<p>========</p><p><b>Due to popular interest this event is <u>f
 ull and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider any of our other open planti
 ngs - we hope to work with you soon!</p><p>========</p><p>Please arrive by&
 nbsp\;<u>9:45am</u>&nbsp\;to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. This 
 planting starts at&nbsp\;<u>10:00am</u>. We provide gloves\, tools\, and pl
 anting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather we
 aring sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>Under 
 age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a paren
 t/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will n
 eed to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">
 youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p>
 <b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our
  number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people 
 at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ine
 ligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocom
 promised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event
  introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their ow
 n household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages
  you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within
  two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftr
 ees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b>
 </a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b
 >Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; O
 ur team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and
  Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@
 friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!
 <br></p><b><hr></b><br>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with Portland
  OIC and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation with support from the Port of Por
 tland\, East Multnomah Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District\, and the Na
 tional Fish &amp\; Wildlife Foundation to restore this two acre parcel of t
 he Slough.<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines an
 d recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any po
 int we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify 
 any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
