DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Day by mulching hundreds of native trees and sh
 rubs that were planted this past winter. We may also take out some weedy in
 troduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-planting a
 t this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u> (great for folks l
 ooking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events help to ensure the highest
  level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><br>Th
 is event is happening in tandem with a FOT free native tree and shrub givea
 way at Happy Valley Park (made possible by funding from State Farm and the 
 Arbor Day Foundation) from 9:30am-12:30pm. See the list of <b><a href="http
 s://drive.google.com/file/d/1bjrAk0uTgPzG6xMwUMlv8nzjCWVJOfnF/view?ts=642f1
 df1">available native plants</a></b>.  Volunteers are eligible to receive u
 p to 4 native trees and/or shrubs (per household). This giveaway is focused
  on volunteers and Clackamas County residents\, though all are welcome. Tre
 es and shrubs will be available on a first-come\, first-served basis. Volun
 teers that arrive early (between 8:30-8:45am) can request that we hold plan
 ts for them to pick up post-stewardship event. <br><br><b>How do I register
 ? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but this event still ha
 s space!  Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.<br><br><b>Plea
 se arrive by 8:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\, stewardship activiti
 es start promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so 
 all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy sh
 oes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<p
 ><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a p
 arent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u
 ><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardi
 an.</p><p><b>What about event safety?</b> Friends of Trees <u>re<u></u>quir
 es</u> that all people at our events cancel if you feel unwell or have been
  exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the e
 vent.  See our safety recommendations and more on the <b><u><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 >Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.              </p><p><b>Questions?  </b>
 Please check out our <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"
 ><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></b>.  Our team is al
 so happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b><
 /u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to working together soon!<br></p><p>===
 <br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://laughingplanet.com/"><u
 ><u>Laughing Planet</u></u></a>.<br>===<br></p><b><hr /></b><p>This event i
 s in partnership with City of Happy Valley.</p>
