DESCRIPTION:Friends of Trees is excited to continue our partnership with th
 e City of Tualatin and Clean Water Services. We will be planting hundreds o
 f native trees and shrubs along a new section of the Tualatin River Greenwa
 y -- <u>your help is what makes this community planting possible</u>! <br><
 br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and c
 offee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We 
 provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dr
 essed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â and be ready to
  have fun! <br><br><b>How do I register?</b> Online registration has now cl
 osed\, but you're still welcome to simply show up!&nbsp\; We'll ask you to 
 sign-in a paper waiver when you arrive. (we close all online registration 2
 4 hrs before an event starts)<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A signed <b><a hr
 ef="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" tar
 get="_blank">youth waiver</a></b> is required for you to volunteer. We ask 
 that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>This pl
 anting is part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than 
 eight million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Cle
 an Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-
 profits\, city partners\, and private landowners will be working together t
 his season to continue the success of this program.<br><br>Please contact J
 enny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@fri
 endsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you ha
 ve questions or need any further information. We look forward to seeing you
  out there!
