DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at West Fowler Woods Trail in partnership
  with the City of Tigard and Clean Water Services.This planting is part of 
 Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more than eight million nati
 ve plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\
 , Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city par
 tners\, and private landowners will be working together this season to cont
 inue the success of this program.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be regi
 stered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We 
 provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, too
 ls and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, c
 losed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a
  group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - c
 lick <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE
 </a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or few
 er -- you can simply show up!\n\nAre you under age 18 and planting without 
 your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/image
 s/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required for you to
  volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by
  an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have a
 ny questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out in
  Tigard!\n\n<i>Accessible on Bus Line 45.  For more directions\, visit <a h
 ref=https://trimet.org/>https://trimet.org/</a>.</i>
