DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of plants that were plant
 ed this past winter at this natural area within the Columbia Slough near Co
 lwood Golf Center! We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if t
 ime allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and thi
 s can be physically-demanding work</u> (great for folks looking for a work 
 out!).  Our stewardship events help to ensure the highest level of plant su
 rvival through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><p><i>**There is a 5 min
 ute walk from the parking area to the planting site - look for our signs to
  guide you!**</i></p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Register by filling out <
 b><a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00001Edi8h&tfa_2189
 =Colwood%20Natural%20Area%20Stewardship\,%20NE%20Portland&tfa_31=a0VPa00000
 DfdE4&tfa_45=%20at%20April%204\,%202026%20at%209:45%20am&tfa_2190=2026-04-0
 4&tfa_49=3.25&tfa_886=Portland%20Parks%20and%20Recreation&tfa_51=offsite" t
 arget="_blank"><u>this quick form</u></a></b>.  Groups\, families\, and ind
 ividuals welcome!</p><u></u><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to find our t
 ent and sign-in\, stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00am. We prov
 ide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dressed fo
 r the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, p
 lease!) and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request tha
 t youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older 
 can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiv
 er form</u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p
 ><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mailto:Volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>vo
 lunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look forward to working together so
 on!<br></p><hr /><p>This event is in partnership with Portland Parks &amp\;
  Recreation and Portland OIC.</p>
