DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/
 crew-leader/"><u>Planting C</u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"><u>rew Leaders</u></a> are trained vol
 unteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading small groups at our c
 ommunity planting events. Friends of Trees can not run these events without
  the support of this valued position!  After your training\, we expect you 
 to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Oct-Nov (select for events
  that fit your schedule!).    <br><br><i>*Please note that we welcome Crew 
 Leaders age 16 and older.<br></i><br>========<br><b><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/crew-leader-training/"><u>Register here</u></a></b> to save yo
 ur place! Space limited.<br>========<br><br><u>This is the hands-on trainin
 g for new Crew Leaders in the Green Space program.  Please note: trainees w
 ill need to have completed the online training before they attend this hand
 s-on session</u>.  The online session will be available for two weeks prior
  for you to complete from home.<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant differe
 nt root stocks\, learn about tree identification\, hone your inclusive lead
 ership skills\, and meet the staff you'll be working alongside!<br><br>Ques
 tions? Please visit the <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-t
