CREATED:20240827T203320Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Help is needed to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs 
 at the unique Gateway Green Park! Join Friends of Trees\, Friends of Gatewa
 y Green\, Portland Parks and Recreation\, and Portland OIC as we enhance th
 e natural area in this unique mountain-biking oasis situated in between I-8
 4 and I-205.</p><p><i>This park is only accessible via the I-205 Multi-Use 
 Path. There is an approximately 10 - 15 minute walk from the **SW corner** 
 of the Fred Meyer parking lot (by the garden center across from The Oregon 
 Clinic) down the multi-use path to our planting site\, look for our signs. 
 Volunteers are encouraged to bike to the planting or take public transporta
 tion to the transit center and walk from there.</i></p><p>Please arrive by 
 9:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 1
 0:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as brea
 kfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up 
 dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to hav
 e fun!<br></p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed a
 t this time\, but there is still room at this event! Please simply follow t
 he directions above to the site\, and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Und
 er age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/g
 uardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to ha
 nd us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blan
 k"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u>
 </u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Transit: </b
 ><span>MAX Green Line with a .2 mile walk.</span></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>
 Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-fa
 q/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assis
 t!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftree
 s.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftre
 es.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look
  forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event spo
 nsor <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u>Portland Gen
 eral Electric</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event made possibl
 e through a grant from the USDA Forest Service. This institution is an equa
 l opportunity provider.</p>
