 to further groups signing-up.</b> We encourage you to consider future Tigar
 d/Tualatin/Sherwood area plantings in the coming weeks\; thank you for your
  understanding.  RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or f
 ewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nFriends of Trees is excited to be planti
 ng at the Tualatin River National Wildlife Refuge! Our partners at this pla
 nting include Friends of the Tualatin River National Wildlife Refuge\, U.S.
  Fish & Wildlife Service\, and Clean Water Services.\n\nThere will be no vo
 lunteer event parking available at the Refuge. Please arrive between 8:30 a
 nd 8:45am to take a shuttle ride to the planting area. The planting will st
 art promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffe
 e\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the wea
 ther and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! \n\nD
 o not hesitate to reach Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have any qu
 estions or need more information. \n\nWe look forward to seeing you out at 
 the Refuge!
