DESCRIPTION:<html-blob>Come out and help plant native trees and shrubs at M
 cKay School Park!&nbsp\; The goal of this event is to&nbsp\;help reduce wee
 dy vegetation and establish a tree canopy to provide more shade and wildlif
 e habitat within the wetland area of this popular park in NE Salem.<br><p>P
 lease arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plan
 ting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance --
  all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes
  or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register? </b>Onli
 ne registration is closed at this time\, but there is still room at this ev
 ent! Please simply show up\, and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Under ag
 e 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/
 guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">yo
 uth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Wha
 t about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our numbe
 r one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our
  events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligibl
 e\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromis
 ed\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event intro
 ductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own hous
 ehold\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you w
 ill need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two w
 eeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&n
 bsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Quest
 ions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our tea
 m is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny
  at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friend
 softrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></
 p><b><hr></b><br>This event is in partnership with the City of Salem.<br><b
 r><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendation
 s made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it i
 s not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers w
 ho are pre-registered.</i></html-blob>
