DESCRIPTION:We are very excited to continue reforesting the transportation 
 corridor that runs from the Columbia River in the North to the City of Glad
 stone in the south. Metro\, ODOT\, BES\, the Port of Portland\, and Columbi
 a Slough Watershed Council are partnering with Friends of Trees to increase
  livability\, habitat and air quality along the I-205 corridor. Friends of 
 Trees will provide morning refreshments\, gloves\, tools\, and all necessar
 y guidance. Please wear sturdy shoes and dress for the weather. \n\nWe look
  forward to seeing you out there!  RSVPs are not required.  Please contact 
 Andy Meeks at AndyM@FriendsofTrees.org or (503) 595-0213 for more informati
 on.
