DESCRIPTION:Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a 
 crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snac
 ks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Pleas
 e come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to ha
 ve fun!\n\n<i>Looking to volunteer as a group?</i> RSVPs are kindly request
 ed for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not req
 uired for groups of 4 or less.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 59
 5-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward 
 to seeing you out there!\n\n<i>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with 
 Friends of Fernhill Wetlands\, the Fernhill Wetlands Council\, and Clean Wa
 ter Services for the second year in Forest Grove. This planting is part of 
 the Tree For All campaign which strives to plant one million native trees a
 nd shrubs during the 2014-2015 planting season within the Tualatin River Wa
 tershed. Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\
 , other non-profits\, City partners\, and private landowners will all be wo
 rking together to make this happen!</i>
