DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees\, Johnson Creek Watershed Council and the
  East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation District for a fun after work\, w
 ork party to help our newly planted trees and shrubs thrive!  We will be do
 ing some light shearing of grass and mulching of recently planted trees.  W
 hat better way to let off some after work steam\, get some exercise\, do so
 me good for your community\, and enjoy a nice afternoon outside?\n\nFOT wil
 l provide snacks\, water\, gloves\, tools and guidance.  All you need to do
  is come wearing clothes you don't mind getting a little dirty\, sturdy sho
 es\, and be ready to sweat a little.  \n\nFor more information about this w
 ork party\, please contact Andy Meeks at 503-595-0213.\n
