DESCRIPTION:==============<br><br><b>Due to popular support\, this event is
  now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider any of our other av
 ailable plantings -- thank you for your consideration!<br><br>=============
 =<br>Help plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs at Bella Casa Natural A
 rea -- it's the support of community members like you who can make this eve
 nt an impactful success!<p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assign
 ed a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tool
 s\, and planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the 
 weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>
 Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a
  parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and 
 will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwa
 iver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br><
 /p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff 
 is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all p
 eople at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those young
 er than 12 and anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for
  the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event i
 ntroductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own 
 household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages y
 ou will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within t
 wo weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></
 a>&nbsp\;for more details.</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please chec
 k out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volu
 nteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; 
 You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look
  forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><br>This planting is poss
 ible with the support of Clackamas County Water Environment Services.<br><b
 r><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendation
 s made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it i
 s not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers w
 ho are pre-registered.</i>
