DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrub
 s that were planted this past winter at this poplar gem of a park! We may a
 lso take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there 
 will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding w
 ork</u> (great for folks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events 
 help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summ
 er months ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>How do I register? </b>Online pre-r
 egistration is closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event!
   Please simply show-up at 9:45am and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Ple
 ase arrive by 9:45am</b><span> to find our tent and sign-in\, stewardship a
 ctivities start promptly at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidan
 ce. All you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturd
 y shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fu
 n!</span></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under vol
 unteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their o
 wn and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthw
 aiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></b
 > signed by their parent/guardian<b>.</b></p><p><b>Transit:</b> Bus Line 25
  with a .2 mile walk.</p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check o
 ut our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank">
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach Cece and Jenny at <a href
 ="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><b
 ><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></a> We look forward to working together soon!<br></p><hr /><p>This even
 t is in partnership with City of Gresham and Portland OIC.</p>
