DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Help ne
 eded to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs in the Rock Creek watersh
 ed in Damascus!</b> Due to extremely limited parking at the planting site\,
  we will be using a shuttle. Please park at the address listed\, and know y
 ou'll be taking a short ~5 min shuttle ride to and from the planting site. 
 Rock Creek is a tributary to the Clackamas River and supports numerous spec
 ies of wildlife\, including salmonids. Thank you for signing-up to make a d
 ifference planting native trees and shrubs!<u></u><br><br><u></u>Please arr
 ive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting star
 ts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well a
 s breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is sh
 ow up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready 
 to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register?</b>&nbsp\;Online registration has
  closed at this time\, but this event still has room for more volunteers!&n
 bsp\; Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.<br><p><b>Under age
  18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/g
 uardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need
  to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><
 u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their par
 ent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require</
 u>&nbsp\;that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or 
 have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days
  of the event.&nbsp\; We&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vac
 cinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and r
 espect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Que
 stions webpage</u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp
 \; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check
  out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u
 ><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is al
 so happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><
 a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftr
 ees.org</u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together 
 soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This project is supported with funding from Clackama
 s County Water Environment Services\, on behalf of Clackamas Service Distri
 ct No. 1.&nbsp\;<br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-bl
