DESCRIPTION:<b>========================</b><br><b>Registration is now CLOSE
 D </b>- <span>Thank you for your interest in attending Crew Leader training
 ! The next opportunity to train for this role will be Fall '25.</span><br><
 br>To be added to a list to receive notice when registration opens for Fall
  trainings\, please email volunteer@friendsoftrees.org\, or simply check ba
 ck on our website.<br><br>For any other questions\, please don't hesitate t
 o contact Jenny and Cece with the Volunteer &amp\; Outreach Program: volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org.<br><b>==========================</b><br><br><a href
 ="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" targe
 t="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>Planting C</u></u></u></u></u></a><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blan
 k"><u><u><u><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></u></u></u></a> are trained volunteer
 s who are crucial to planting trees and leading small group at our communit
 y planting events. Friends of Trees cannot run these events without the sup
 port of this valued position!  After your training\, we expect you to help 
 lead a crew at 3 Saturday morning events Jan-April (select for events that 
 fit your schedule!).    <br><br><u>This is an In-Person training for new Cr
 ew Leaders in the Green Space program.  Please note: trainees will need to 
 have completed the online training before they attend this session</u>.  Th
 e online session will be sent to you and available for two weeks.<br><br><b
 r>Trainees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn about tree ide
 ntification\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet the staff yo
 u'll be working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_bl
 ank"><u><u><u><u><u>Planting Crew Leader webpage</u></u></u></u></u></a> or
  contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u>
 <u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-
 0-213  We hope to work with you in this important role!<b><br><hr /></b><p>
 This event made possible through a grant from the USDA Forest Service. This
  institution is an equal opportunity provider.</p>
