DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at the second of two plantings at Woodhav
 en City Park this season! \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered 
 and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide
  breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and 
 guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and 
 get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are
  kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs 
 are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply 
 show up!\n\nThis planting is in partnership with\, Tualatin Riverkeepers\, 
 the City of Sherwood\, and Clean Water Services. This planting is also part
  of the Tree For All campaign which has planted over three million native p
 lants in the Tualatin River Watershed in the past decade! Clean Water Servi
 ces\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city
  partners\, and private landowners will be working together this season to 
 continue the success of this program.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (
 503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look f
 orward to seeing you out there!
