DESCRIPTION:===============<u></u><u></u><u></u>==<br><br><b>This community
  planting has been canceled.</b>&nbsp\; Covid-19 transmission still remains
  a concern for our staff and planting partners.&nbsp\; Out of an abundance 
 of caution\, we will not be gathering a group from the public to plant at t
 his event.&nbsp\; We apologize to everyone who has signed up for this incon
 venience\, and hope to plant with you when it’s a little safer!<br><br>====
 ===========<u></u><u></u><u></u>==<br><br>Join Friends of Trees and the Cit
 y of Happy Valley as we plant native trees and shrubs to help restore the r
 iparian vegetation around Mt. Scott Creek. Mt. Scott is a tributary to Kell
 og Creek\, an important tributary to the Willamette River and home to Coho 
 salmon\, Steelhead\, Pacific lamprey and many more wildlife species.<br><br
 ><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is ou
 r number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people
  at our events bring and wear a fabric face mask\, respect 6' or more of di
 stance from others not in their own household\, and follow a few other prot
 ocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Aske<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>d-Questions webpa
 ge</a></b>.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 
 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u
 ></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>.&nbsp\
 ; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to include th
 eir parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>'s contact information when they 
 register online.<br><br><b>Question<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>s?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<
 /b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to a
 ssist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at&nbsp\;<a href="mai
 lto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@fr<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>ien
 dsoftrees.or<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>
 <u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>g</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to seein
 g you out there!<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guideli
 nes and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at 
 any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and n
 otify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
