DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and our partners to celebrate National Po
 llinators Week this June! <br><br>This is the second of two community works
 hops to learn about local pollinators\, how to steward healthy pollinator h
 abitats\, and get a chance to see these awesome flora and fauna in action. 
 This workshop is free to the public\, and will be held indoors with an outd
 oors component. Materials will be provided for participants\, just bring yo
 urself!<b><br></b><br><b>How do I register? </b>Register by filling out <b>
 <a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00000AvdNT&tfa_2189=P
 ollinator%20Workshop\,%20Sherwood&tfa_31=a0VPa000002at01&tfa_45=%20at%20Jun
 e%2018\,%202024%20at%201:00%20pm&tfa_2190=2024-06-18&tfa_49=2&tfa_886=Stand
 ard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>this quic
 k form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b>.<br><br>Prepare for a brief 
 guided garden tour and to come home with a native plant to steward healthy 
 pollinator habitat in your local community here in Washington County. <br><
 br>This workshop is made possible by funding from Tualatin Soil &amp\; Wate
 r Conservation District.
