DESCRIPTION:<p>======</p><p><b><u>Due to popular interest\, this event is f
 ull and closed</u></b>. Please consider our next Hillsboro plantings -- two
  to select from on Sat\, Dec 6th! </p><p>======</p><p><b>Help needed to pla
 nt hundreds of native trees and shrubs at our final weekend of planting at 
 Jackson Bottom Wetlands this season! </b>Plant hundreds of native trees and
  shrubs before the rainy season comes and the wetlands are submerged in wat
 er for the winter!</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned
  a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\
 , and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot ch
 ocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing st
 urdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><i>**Please note: the
 re is a 10 minute walk from the parking area to where we'll be planting. Pl
 ease plan your timing accordingly.</i></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We reques
 t that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and o
 lder can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="h
 ttp://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>you
 th waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/g
 uardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https
 ://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>Vol
 unteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also h
 appy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@
 friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward 
 to planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event in partnership wit
 h Clean Water Services.<br></p>
