DESCRIPTION:<br>~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br><b>Thank you for all your support\,</b>
  <b>due to popular interest this event is now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&n
 bsp\; Thank you for your interest and please consider joining any of our ot
 her open planting events during the month of November-- we hope to work wit
 h you soon!<br><br>~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>Your help is needed to help plant trees 
 and shrubs at McKay School Park in NE Salem! Friends of Trees in partnershi
 p with the City of Salem is undertaking a multi-year effort at McKay to hel
 p reduce weedy vegetation and establish a tree canopy to provide more shade
  and wildlife habitat within the wetland area of the park. Your support wil
 l contribute to greening this school area and park for generations to come!
 <br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats 
 and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts at 9:00am. We prov
 ide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up
  dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to ha
 ve fun!<br><br><b><u>Under age 18?</u></b> A signed youth waiver is require
 d for you to volunteer: <b><a href="http://www.friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiv
 er">www.friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver</a></b> We ask that youth 15 years a
 nd younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo
 \, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.
 org">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any fur
 ther information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
