DESCRIPTION:<p>Your help is needed to help plant at Wapato Lake National Wi
 ldlife Refuge\, one of the nation's newest refuges! This site consists of 8
 17 acres within a 5\,000 acre network of near-contiguous publicly-owned nat
 ural areas connecting wetlands\, floodplains\, and waterways\, is of critic
 al importance to the health of water\, wildlife and people across the Portl
 and metro area.<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigne
 d a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools
 \, and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot choc
 olate. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes
 /boots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Ho
 w do I register? </b>Onlin<u></u><u></u>e registration has closed at this t
 ime\, but there is still room at this event\, please simply <u>show up at 8
 :45am</u> and sign-in when you arrive. The walk to this site is quite wet\,
  it is highly recommended to wear waterproof boots if you have them. <br><b
 r><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a 
 parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will ne
 ed to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" targe
 t="_blank"><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></a></u></b> signed by their pare
 nt/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="h
 ttps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u>Volunteer F
 AQ webpage</u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can
  reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" targ
 et="_blank"><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></a>\, 503-595
 -0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr /></b><p>T
 his event is in partnership with Clean Water Services.</p>
