UID:5ufr9o2l6l88j71ce054ndpof6@google.com
CREATED:20190828T204708Z
DESCRIPTION:<span><span></span>=====================<br></span>&nbsp\;<br><
 span></span><br>Based on recent recommendations from health officials throu
 ghout the region\, <span><u>we are cancelling this Saturday's Happy Valley 
 Park planting.</u>&nbsp\;</span> We’refollowing the advice to create social
  distance and not voluntarily bringing a large group of people together. <b
 r><br><span>We apologize for this inconvenience and ask for your understand
 ing as we try to <span><span>do our part to diminish the risk of COVID-19 s
 preading in the community.</span></span><br><br>=====================&nbsp\
 ;&nbsp\;</span><i><br></i><br>Let's plant trees together in Happy Valley!&n
 bsp\; Your help is needed to plant native trees and shrubs to restore the r
 iparian vegetation around Mt. Scott Creek. Mt. Scott is a tributary to Kell
 og Creek\, an important tributary to the Willamette River and home to Coho 
 salmon\, Steelhead\, Pacific lamprey and many more wildlife species. The tr
 ees and shrubs you plant will help cool the water so our salmonoid friends 
 and other species can continue to flourish in this urban area!&nbsp\; This 
 event is supported by the City of Happy Valley.<br><br>Please arrive by 8:4
