DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at the first of four plantings to help re
 vitalize Hall Creek in the heart of Beaverton. These plantings are part of 
 a broader creek restoration project being completed by the City to improve 
 water quality and beautify the area. The plantings are in partnership with 
 the City of Beaverton and Clean Water Services and supported by a Metro vot
 er-approved Nature in Neighborhoods grant.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am t
 o be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:
 00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as glo
 ves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing s
 turdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a grou
 p?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click 
 <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE<
 /a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewe
 r -- you can simply show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-
 0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to
  seeing you out there!
