DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at the first of two plantings this season
  at King City Park!\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and ass
 igned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakf
 ast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidanc
 e. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get rea
 dy to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly
  requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendso
 ftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not
  required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up
 !\n\nThis event is in partnership with King City and and Clean Water Servic
 es. This planting is part of the Tree For All campaign which has planted ov
 er three million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed in the past 
 decade! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\,
  other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners will be working
  together this season to continue the success of this program.\n\nPlease co
 ntact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need mo
 re information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
