DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><span><span><p>========</p><p><b>Due to popular inte
 rest this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider our P
 ortland Neighborhood Trees planting happening this same day - we hope to wo
 rk with you soon!</p><p>========</p></span></span>Help plant hundreds of na
 tive trees and shrubs at this special site at the entrance of the beautiful
  Columbia River Gorge!&nbsp\;<br><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and 
 be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide glov
 es\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed
  for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<
 br><br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under
  volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer 
 on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their pare
 nt/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of voluntee
 rs and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiri
 ng that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception o
 f those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\
 ;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mas
 k through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from oth
 ers not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other 
 snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household 
 feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Qu
 estions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbs
 p\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;
 <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpag
 e</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Ga
 briel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to plan
 ting together soon!<br></p><b><hr><br></b>Friends of Trees is partnering wi
 th the Sandy River Watershed Council and Friends of the Sandy River Delta w
 ith support from the US Forest Service to continue native seedling planting
 s at the Sandy River Delta.<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow 
 the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Author
 ity. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel
  them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i><u></u><br><u></
 u><i><br></i><u></u><br><u></u>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors&nbsp\
 ;<a href="https://www.nba.com/blazers/">Portland Trailblazers</a>&nbsp\;&am
 p\; <a href="https://daimler-trucksnorthamerica.com/">Daimler Truck North A
 merica</a>!<br>===<i><br></i><u></u></html-blob>
