DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and the City of Salem for the third of th
 is yearâs three planting events at the newly opened Minto Island Conserva
 tion Area across the Minto Island Bridge! We will be planting native trees 
 and shrubs along the new multi-use path connecting Riverfront Park with the
  greater Minto Brown Island Park. This event is partially funded with grant
 s from Oregon Watershed Enhancement Board and Meyer Memorial Trust.<br><br>
 Volunteer parking will be at Riverfront City Park.  You're welcome to park 
 in the Carousel parking lot or the larger lot along Water Street.  Either w
 ay there will be a short 5-10 min walk across the newly opened bridge to wh
 ere we'll be planting.  Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered and as
 signed to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide break
 fast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidan
 ce. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe sho
 es and get ready to have fun! <br><br><b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</
 b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a h
 ref="https://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Ffriendsoftrees.org%2Fvolunte
 ering%2Fgroup-registration&amp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=1519343719129000&amp\;usg=AFQ
 jCNExRBZaMvmNHtf5tZiF5MhltsDjhw" target="_blank">HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs a
 re not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply s
 how up!<br><br>Are you under age 18 and planting without your parent/guardi
 an?  A signed <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.friend
 softrees.org%2Fimages%2Fstories%2Fpdf%2FYouth_Waiver_2015.pdf&amp\;sa=D&amp
 \;ust=1519343719129000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNHXFKcpcabs8lIyO90X1pSx0ogdNw" target=
 "_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We kindly reque
 st youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br><br>Pleas
 e contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or nee
 d more information. <br><br>We look forward to seeing you in Salem!<br><br>
 ===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a href="https://www.google.com/url
 ?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2F%2F&amp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=1519343719129000&amp\
 ;usg=AFQjCNEWlCYH5-jfHw7zQD_JSZaQ_bxX_A" target="_blank">REI</a>!<br>===
