DESCRIPTION:<p>=========</p><p><b><u>This event is continuing as planned</u
 ></b>.  Local forecasters are calling for melting snow/ice through Friday a
 fternoon/evening.  We are confident road conditions near this site will be 
 safe for this event.  FOT acknowledges that road conditions vary depending 
 on where one lives.  If you decide it's not the right decision for you to a
 ttend\, please know we 100% respect your decision.  Please prioritize your 
 safety!</p><p>=========</p><br><span>Bybee Lakes Hope Center is a transitio
 nal housing facility in North Portland supporting people experiencing homel
 essness. They have a 5 acre Victory Garden\, run by VETRest with a young fr
 uit orchard\, a thriving vegetable garden\, and a walking path with a varie
 ty of large stock trees planted by Friends of Trees in 2021. For this event
  we are partnering with VETRest to plant hundreds of native shrubs and a na
 tive wildflower meadow for residents to enjoy!</span><p>Please arrive by 9:
 45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 10:
 00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakf
 ast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dr
 essed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have 
 fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under voluntee
 r with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own an
 d will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiv
 er" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u><
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/
 guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="http
 s://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and
  Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u>
 <u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to 
 planting together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a hre
 f="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Portland General 
 Electric</u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p><br></p>
