DESCRIPTION:<p><b>====================</b></p><p><b>This event is now full 
 and closed</b>. Please consider our third Jackson Bottom event on Saturday\
 , Oct 25th. <b></b></p><p><b>=====================</b></p><p><b>Your help i
 s needed to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs at the beautiful Jack
 son Bottom Wetlands Preserve\, an amazing and unique wildlife preserve. </b
 >Jackson Bottom is a 635-acre wetland complex on the Tualatin River that is
  designated as an Important Bird Area for both migrating and non-migratory 
 species. </p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planti
 ng crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and pla
 nting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -
 - all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoe
 s or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><i>**Please note: there is a 1
 0 minute walk from the parking area to where we'll be planting. Please plan
  your timing accordingly.</i></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that yo
 uth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can 
 volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://fri
 endsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u>youth waiver form</u></a></
 u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please che
 ck out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target
 ="_blank"><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy
  to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@frie
 ndsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b><
 /a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr />
 </b><p><br>This event is in partnership with the City of Hillsboro.</p>
