CREATED:20260123T231648Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Week by mulching hundreds of native plants that
  were planted this past winter at Nadaka Nature Park! We may also take out 
 some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there will be no tr
 ee-planting at this event\, and this can be physically-demanding work</u> (
 great for folks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events help to e
 nsure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer months
  ahead.<br><p><b>How do I register? </b>Register by filling out <b><a href=
 "https://www.tfaforms.com/4840511?tfa_26=a0TPa00001Edi8k&tfa_2189=Nadaka%20
 Nature%20Park%20Stewardship\,%20Gresham&tfa_31=a0VPa00000DfdED&tfa_45=%20at
 %20April%2018\,%202026%20at%209:45%20am&tfa_2190=2026-04-18&tfa_49=3.25&tfa
 _886=Standard%20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>this quick 
 form</u></u></u></u></a></b>.  Groups\, families\, and individuals welcome!
 </p><u></u><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\,
  stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tool
 s\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and
  wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be re
 ady to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and un
 der volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on 
 their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org
 /youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form<
 /u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian
 .</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>
 <u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist! <a href="mailto:Voluntee
 r@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><
 u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></a> / 503-595-0213 We look forward to working togethe
 r soon!</p><hr /><p>This event is in partnership with City of Gresham and P
 ortland OIC.</p>
