DESCRIPTION:Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting
  trees properly and leading groups of volunteers <u></u>at&nbsp\; planting<
 u></u> events this coming planting season! Friends of Trees is aiming to pl
 ant tens of thousands of native trees and shrubs at more than 50 public pla
 nting events in the Green Space Program. Help make those goals a reality an
 d register to become a Crew Leader!<br><br>The training is free (and includ
 es lunch and a t-shirt!) but registration is required.&nbsp\; Register&nbsp
 \; <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/portland-vancouver-crew-leader-train
 ing/" target="_blank">HERE</a> to train for this popular role.&nbsp\; Spots
  are limited and this training will fill-up so <a href="https://friendsoftr
 ees.org/portland-vancouver-crew-leader-training/" target="_blank">register 
 now!</a><br><br>Please contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you need
  more information. We look forward to answering any questions you may have!
