DESCRIPTION:<p>Join Friends of Trees for some planting fun in Aloha -- you'
 ll be planting native trees\, shrubs\, and wildflowers along Butternut Cree
 k adjacent to Deline HOA. We will be partnering with Clean Water Services\,
  Tualatin Soil and Water Conservation District\, and Native Plantscapes NW 
 in this effort. </p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a
  planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, 
 and guidance\, as well as light breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocola
 te. We ask that all volunteers dress for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes/bo
 ots you don't mind getting dirty\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>H
 ow do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but the
 re is still room at this event!  Please simply show up and sign-in when you
  arrive.  <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under v
 olunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their
  own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/yo
 uthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></a></u></b> sign
 ed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our 
 <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><
 u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to 
 assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendso
 ftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></
 u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><
 b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with Clean Water Services.</p>
