DESCRIPTION:<p>========</p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is <u
 >full and closed</u>.  </b>Please consider signing-up for our North Portlan
 d Neighborhood Trees event on Sat\, Dec 6th!</p><p>========</p><p><br></p><
 p><b>Wilkes Creek is one of the last remaining surface creeks providing cle
 an\, cold water directly to the Columbia Slough\, and we need your help to 
 protect it! </b>Come to this event and help plant hundreds of native wildfl
 owers to enhance pollinator habitat and protect the Columbia Slough watersh
 ed.</p><p>Please arrive by 9:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting cre
 w. The planting starts at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting
  guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all
  you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or 
 boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request tha
 t youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older 
 can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http:/
 /friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u>
 </a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Plea
 se check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" 
 target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</
 u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is al
 so happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b
 ><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward to planting together soon!</p
 ><p>===</p><p>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a href="https://wyldcanna.c
 om/" target="_blank"><u>WYLD</u></a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b>
