CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:<b>**UPDATE: This event is now FULL.**</b>  Thank you for your 
 interest!  If you would like to attend another planting event in Happy Vall
 ey on the same day\, Friends of Trees is also hosting a planting at Happy V
 alley Park\, March 15th\, 8:45am - 1:00pm.  Please see our full description
  for this fun alternative on our calendar.\n\nJoin the Rock Creek Partnersh
 ip on Saturday\, March 15th in Happy Valley for its third annual Watershed 
 Wide Event!  Weâll be removing invasive vegetation\, mulching\, and plant
 ing native trees and shrubs at three streamside sites to help improve the w
 ater quality in the Rock Creek basin -- and weâd love your help!  No expe
 rience is necessary and we welcome families\, neighbors\, and friends!  We 
 provide the gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weathe
 r and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nThere will be live
  music\, a delicious variety of breakfast and lunch goodies\, and raffle pr
 izes! The staging site will once again be the Galaxy Barn at Pendarvis Farm
  - site of the renowned Pickathon Music Festival.  The event will begin pro
 mptly at 9:00am\, so we ask for everyone to arrive by 8:45am to the staging
  site to get registered and assigned to a crew\, as well as to enjoy hot co
 ffee and breakfast treats. The event will wrap-up around 1:00pm.\n\nRock Cr
 eek is an important tributary of the Clackamas River\, which provides high 
 quality drinking water to more than 300\,000 people and provides critical h
 abitat for many sensitive species of plants\, fish and wildlife.  \n\nPleas
 e contact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need 
 more information.\n
