CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:This Planting is part of the Tree for All campaign and is in pa
 rtnership with the city of Beaverton and Clean Water Services. We will be p
 lanting live stakes and containerized trees and shrubs\, restoring the ripa
 rian area along Summer Creek. The ambitious goal of Tree for All is to plan
 t two million trees in the Tualatin River Valley in 20 years.\n\nThis plant
 ing is located in a very wet area - please bring waterproof/rubber boots if
  you have them.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigne
 d to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfa
 st snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance
 . Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get read
 y to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 peop
 le - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/group-registrati
 on-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.   Please contact Andy or Jenny at (503) 
 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. \n
