DESCRIPTION:Help plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs in the Rock Cree
 k watershed in Damascus! Due to extremely limited parking at the planting s
 ite\, we will be using a shuttle. Please know you'll be taking a short 2 mi
 les shuttle ride from this listed address to the planting site.<br><p>Pleas
 e arrive by 8:40am to catch the shuttle\, sign-in\, and be assigned a plant
 ing crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and pl
 anting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather we
 aring sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I 
 register?&nbsp\;</b>Online registration is now closed for this event\, but 
 there is still room for you to join! Please simply show up and sign-in at t
 he registration table.</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that you
 th 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older
  can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signe
 d by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The saf
 ety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees.
  We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with 
 the exception of those younger than 12 and anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocomp
 romised and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a f
 ace mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance f
 rom others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any
  other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your hou
 sehold feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently A
 sked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp
 \;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<
 b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gab
 riel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.
 org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to plant
 ing together soon!</p><b><hr><br></b>This project is supported with funding
  from Clackamas County Water Environment Services\, on behalf of Clackamas 
 Service District No. 1.<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the 
 guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority.
  If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel the
 m and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
