DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Your help is needed to help 
 plant at Wapato Lake National Wildlife Refuge\, one of the nation's newest 
 refuges!</b>&nbsp\;This site consists of 817 acres within a 5\,000 acre net
 work of near-contiguous publicly-owned natural areas connecting wetlands\, 
 floodplains\, and waterways\, is of critical importance to the health of wa
 ter\, wildlife and people across the Portland metro area.&nbsp\;<u></u><br>
 <br><u></u><u></u>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a plan
 ting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and p
 lanting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate
  -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy sh
 oes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><u></u><u></u><br><u></u>*Expec
 t a ~<u>15 minute walk</u>&nbsp\;from parking area to the planting site.*<b
 r><br><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time
 \, but this event still has room for more planting volunteers -- please sim
 ply show up and sign-in when you arrive!<br><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;W
 e request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; 
 Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nb
 sp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u>youth waive
 r form</u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>
 What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require</u>&nbsp\;that all peopl
 e at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to so
 meone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; W
 e&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wea
 r a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical d
 istance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vol
 unteer-faq/"><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></a>
 </u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><
 p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="
 https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u><
 /u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can re
 ach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftre
 es.org"><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We loo
 k forward to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p>This planting is in p
 artnership with Clean Water Services and the United States Fish and Wildlif
 e Service.&nbsp\;</p><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
