DESCRIPTION:===============<u></u><u></u><u></u>==<br><br><b>This community
  planting has been canceled.</b>&nbsp\; Covid-19 transmission still remains
  a concern for our staff and planting partners.&nbsp\; Out of an abundance 
 of caution\, we will not be gathering a group from the public to plant at t
 his event.&nbsp\; We apologize to everyone who has signed up for this incon
 venience\, and hope to plant with you when it’s a little safer!<br><br>====
 ===========<u></u><u></u><u></u>==<br><br>This planting in SE Portland is p
 art of Johnson Creek Watershed Council's Watershed Wide Event! Come plant n
 ative trees and shrubs to help restore the Johnson Creek Watershed's native
  habitats and improve water quality. This project is in partnership with th
 e Johnson Creek Watershed Council and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation with
  support from Clackamas County Water Environment Services.<br><br><b>What a
 bout Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number o
 ne priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our ev
 ents bring and wear a fabric face mask\, respect 6' or more of distance fro
 m others not in their own household\, and follow a few other protocols\, ou
 tlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">
 Volunteer Frequently-Aske<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>d-Questions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\
 ;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volu
 nteer with a parent/guardian<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can
  volunteer on their own and will need to include their parent/guardian<u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u>
 </u><u></u>'s contact information when they register online.<br><br><b>Ques
 tion<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u></u>s?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a hr
 ef="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b
 >.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pa
 blo\, and Carey at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>v
 olunteer@fr<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><
 u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></
 u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u>g</b></a>&nbsp\;W
 e look forward to seeing you out there!<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continue
 s to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon H
 ealth Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we
  will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
