CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:Join the work party to plant native trees and shrubs and remove
  invasive species including Himalayan Blackberry and English Ivy!\n\nPlease
  arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event wi
 ll start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/
 coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for th
 e weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking
  to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more
  than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group
 -registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or 
 groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nFriends of trees is exci
 ted to partner with Portland OIC\, Portland Parks & Recreation\, the Columb
 ia Slough Watershed Council\, and Friends of the Columbia Children's Arbore
 tum with support from the Port of Portland\, Metro\, and East Multnomah Soi
 l & Water Conservation District to restore a part of one of NE Portland's "
 hidden gems": the Columbia Children's Arboretum. \n\nPlease contact Jenny o
 r Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more informatio
 n. We look forward to seeing you out there!\n\n<b>Special thanks to the Por
 t of Portland for generously sponsoring this event.</b>
