DESCRIPTION:As part of the Rock Creek Partnership with SOLVE and the Clacka
 mas River Basin Council\, Friends of Trees is leading volunteer restoration
  events along the banks of Rock Creek and its tributaries. Rock Creek is a 
 tributary to the Clackamas River and supports numerous species of wildlife\
 , including salmonids. This project is supported with funding from Clackama
 s County Water Environment Services\, on behalf of Clackamas Service Distri
 ct No. 1. \n\nPlease meet by 8:30-8:45am at the staging site listed above. 
  A short shuttle ride will take volunteers to the planting location.  The p
 lanting will start at 9:00am and be completed no later than 1pm. We provide
  breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and 
 guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and 
 get ready to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs ar
 e kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://
 friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs
  are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply
  show up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have an
 y questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out the
 re!
