DESCRIPTION:==============<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this event i
 s now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Thank you for your planting suppor
 t\, and please consider any of our other open planting events!<br><br>=====
 =========<br><br>Join Friends of Trees for the first of two plantings with 
 the City of Beaverton to plant trees\, shrubs\, and wildflowers along Fanno
  Creek Greenway!<p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a pla
 nting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and 
 planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather 
 wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under ag
 e 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/
 guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">yo
 uth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b
 >What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our n
 umber one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at
  our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those younger than 
 12 and anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised and not eligible for the vac
 cine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introduct
 ions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own househol
 d\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will 
 need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks
  of this event.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nb
 sp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/v
 olunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy
  to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a hr
 ef="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b
 ></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!</p><br><b><hr><br></
 b>This event is in partnership with the City of Beaverton and Clean Water S
 ervices\, and is part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted mor
 e than ten million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005
 !<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recomme
 ndations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we fe
 el it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volun
 teers who are pre-registered.</i><br><i><br></i><br>===<br>Thank you to our
  event sponsor&nbsp\;<a href="https://getchipdrop.com/" id="ow4474" __is_ow
 ner="true">Chipdrop</a> !<br>===&nbsp\;<i><br></i>
