DESCRIPTION:=============<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this event is
  now <u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider any of the other op
 en events -- thank you for your interest!<br><br>=============<br><br>Kick 
 off the new year by planting hundreds of native trees and shrubs with Frien
 ds of Trees in Beaverton!&nbsp\; This event will help restore the Churchill
  Forest natural area to a diverse and healthy riparian forest and ephemeral
  wetland.&nbsp\;<p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a pla
 nting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and 
 planting guidance -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather 
 wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under ag
 e 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/
 guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">yo
 uth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b
 >What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our n
 umber one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at
  our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineli
 gible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompr
 omised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event i
 ntroductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own 
 household\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages y
 ou will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within t
 wo weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></
 a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Q
 uestions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://f
 riendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our
  team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and J
 enny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<b
 r></p><b><hr></b><br>This planting is in partnership with the City of Beave
 rton and Clean Water Services\, and part of Tree For All\, a partnership wh
 ich has planted more than ten million native plants in the Tualatin River W
 atershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of
  volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners wi
 ll be working together this season to continue the success of this program.
 &nbsp\;<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and r
 ecommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point
  we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any
  volunteers who are pre-registered.</i>
