DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========================================</b></p><p><b>Due
  to popular interest\, this event is </b><u>full and closed.</u> Please con
 sider our 4/12 Northgate + D Street Park neighborhood planting.</p><p><b>==
 ======================================</b></p><p>Help is needed to help pla
 nt hundreds of native trees and shrubs at McKay City Park in NE Salem! In p
 artnership with the City of Salem\, Friends of Trees is undertaking a multi
 -year effort at McKay to help reduce weedy vegetation and establish a tree 
 canopy to provide more shade and wildlife habitat within the wetland area o
 f the park. <br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a
  planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, 
 and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot choc
 olate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing stur
 dy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We
  request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a 
 href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u>youth wa
 iver form</u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Tra
 nsit:</b> B<span>us Route 11 with a .5 mile walk.</span></p><p><b>Questions
 ?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volun
 teer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></a></u></b>.
   Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a hre
 f="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><b><u>volunteer@
 friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to plan
 ting together soon!</p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href=
 "https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Port
 land General Electric</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b>
 <hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with the City of Salem.</p>
