CREATED:20210813T213316Z
DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>Help plant native trees and shrubs and removi
 ng invasive species including Himalayan Blackberry and English Ivy at this 
 popular park in NE Portland! Please note the start time for this event is a
 n hour later than most of our events.<br><p>Please arrive by <u>9:45am</u> 
 to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at <u>10:00
 am</u>. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need t
 o do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and
  be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>How do I register?</b> Online registration 
 is closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event. Please simp
 ly show up and sign-in when you arrive.&nbsp\; Thanks!</p><p><b>Under age 1
 8?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/gua
 rdian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need t
 o hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth
  waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b>Wh
 at about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our numb
 er one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at ou
 r events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligib
 le\, such as children younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromi
 sed\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event intr
 oductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own hou
 sehold\, bring your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you 
 will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household feels unwell within two 
 weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.o
 rg/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&
 nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Ques
 tions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://frie
 ndsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our te
 am is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenn
 y at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@frien
 dsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br><
 /p><b><hr><br></b>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with Portland OIC\
 , Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation\, the Columbia Slough Watershed Council\
 , and Friends of the Columbia Children's Arboretum with support from the Po
 rt of Portland\, East Multnomah Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District\, a
 nd the Portland Clean Energy Fund to restore a part of one of NE Portland's
  "hidden gems": the Columbia Children's Arboretum.<br><br><i>Friends of Tre
 es continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC a
 nd Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host 
 events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-register
 ed.</i><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
