 ! This is the first of two plantings this season where we will be in a port
 ion of the refuge not open to the public\, so take advantage of this opport
 unity to see a side of the refuge that few get to experience! Our partners 
 at this planting include Friends of the Tualatin River National Wildlife Re
 fuge\, U.S. Fish & Wildlife Service\, and Clean Water Services.\n\nPlease a
 rrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will
  start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/co
 ffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the 
 weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Due to hi
 gh demand\, this event is now closed to future sign-ups</b> Thank you for y
 our interest and please consider joining us at another of our planting even
 ts!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any ques
 tions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
