 r event that looks like a good fit for your interests and schedule!<br><br>
 <b>=======</b><br><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Come plant native trees an
 d shrubs to help restore the Johnson Creek Watershed's native habitats and 
 improve water quality.</b> This planting in SE Portland is part of Johnson 
 Creek Watershed Council's Watershed Wide Event. Lunch will be provided at a
 n afternoon celebration at a different location if you wish to join.<u></u>
 <br><br><u></u>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a plantin
 g crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and plan
 ting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate --
  all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes
  or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<b><br></b><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We 
