 T&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank">RSVPs kindly requested</a>.<br>Please arr
 ive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\,
  or hot chocolate. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide glove
 s\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the
  weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â and be ready to have fun! <b
 r><br><b>How do I register?</b> All individuals and groups are kindly asked
  to RSVP to save your spot(s) by filling out our quick <a href="https://www
 .tfaforms.com/4694015?tfa_26=a0Tf4000003IH95&tfa_28=Happy%20Valley%20Height
 s%20Natural%20Area\,%20Happy%20Valley&tfa_31=a0Vf40000045Nku&tfa_45=Tree%20
 Planter\,%202/9/2019%208:45AM%20&tfa_47=2019-02-09&tfa_49=4&tfa_59=Standard
 %20FOT&tfa_51=offsite" target="_blank">Registration Form</a>. Registration 
 is highly recommended but not required.<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> A signe
 d <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.p
 df" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We a
 sk that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Plea
 se contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:v
 olunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</
 a> if you have questions or need any further information. We look forward t
 o seeing you out there!
