DESCRIPTION:In partnership with the Dharma Rain Zen Center with support by 
 East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation District\, Metro\, and the Nationa
 l Fish & Wildlife Foundation\, Friends of Trees is honored to be part of th
 e third year of plant revegetation work occurring in this neglected parcel 
 of Northeast Portland.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and 
 assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide bre
 akfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guid
 ance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get 
 ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kin
 dly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are 
 not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show
  up!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any que
 stions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
