DESCRIPTION:=================<br><br><b>Due to popular interest\, this even
 t is now <u>full and closed</u>.&nbsp\;</b> Please consider any of our futu
 re events that remain open - we hope to plant with you soon!<br><br>=======
 ==========<br><br>Help plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs at Jackson
  Bottom Wetlands Preserve! Please note: there will be an approximately 10-1
 5 min walk from the parking lot to the planting area.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<
 b><br></b><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers an
 d staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring th
 at all people at our events bring and wear a fabric face mask\, respect 6' 
 or more of distance from others not in their own household\,&nbsp\; bringin
 g your own water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, a
 nd follow a few other protocols\, outlined on our <b><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Asked-Questions webpage<
 /a></b>.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 
 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can v
 olunteer on their own and will need to include their parent/guardian's cont
 act information when they register online.<br><br>This is the first of two 
 plantings this season at Jackson Bottom in partnership with the City of Hil
 lsboro and Clean Water Services. This planting is part of Tree For All\, a 
 partnership that has planted more than ten million native plants in the Tua
 latin River Watershed since 2005!&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Questions?&nbsp\;
  </b>Please check out our <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-
 faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assis
 t!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at <a href="mailto:Volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org" id="ow828" __is_owner="true"><b>volunteer@friendsof
 trees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to seeing you out there!&nbsp\; &nb
 sp\;&nbsp\;<br><br><br><p><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guide
 lines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If a
 t any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and
  notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i></p>
