CREATED:20200810T222212Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Friends of Trees\, in partnership with the City of Tualatin 
 and Clean Water Services\, is excited to be providing an opportunity for th
 e community to get outside and give back in a safe\, physically-distanced w
 ay. Throughout this scheduled week\, pre-registered volunteers will be help
 ing mulch recently-planted native trees\, shrubs\, and plants at Brown’s Fe
 rry Park! Mulching is an important step to ensure the survival of these new
  friends during the tough summer conditions.&nbsp\;To reduce the risks of s
 preading COVID-19 among volunteers and staff\, there are a number of adjust
 ments that have been made. Please read all of the details below before sign
 ing up for a shift.&nbsp\;While we love to have fun at our events\, we take
  our volunteer and staff safety very seriously. Thank you for your understa
 nding and patience as we pilot this revised program to continue this work u
 nder the limiting conditions we have.</p><ul><li><p>We are recruiting for m
 ultiple volunteer shifts between Saturday\, 8/15 through Friday\, 8/21.</p>
 </li><li><p><b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.secure.force.com/voluntee
 rs/" id="ow5485" __is_owner="true">Pre-registration</a> is required</u>.</b
 >&nbsp\;In order to volunteer\, you must reserve your spot on a shift and&n
 bsp\;<b>show up at that time.</b></p></li><li><p><b>Only one individual (or
  household) is allowed per volunteer shift.</b>&nbsp\;To minimize exposure 
 between multiple households\, we are limiting one household per volunteer s
 hift.</p><ul><li><p>When we say household\, this could be with housemates o
 r family members that share the same home. You can also volunteer solo!</p>
 </li><li><p>No staff member will be present. For any youth age 16 or older 
 hoping to volunteer on their own\, a contact number of a legal guardian wil
 l be required so that we can confirm details and permission via phone. If y
 ou are an adult signing up your child\, there are instructions in the waive
 r/registration form for you to register them.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><b>E
 very volunteer from the household must sign a waiver prior to their shift</
 b>:&nbsp\;In addition to your registration and waiver\, each member of your
  household will need to have a signed waiver before volunteering for the de
 signated shift.&nbsp\; Please ask us if have any questions with registering
  online.</p></li><li><p>By signing up\, you also agree to&nbsp\;<b>honor th
 e shift that you have signed up for</b><b>.</b>&nbsp\;For this operation to
  be successful\, it is important that you are on site only within your shif
 t time. This is to minimize any overlap between shifts and ensure that only
  one household is volunteering at a time. Again\, this is for the safety of
  all.</p></li><li><p><b>Face coverings are required.</b></p></li><li><b><b>
 🌳 📝 🌟To view available shifts and sign up\, visit the<a href="https://fr
 iendsoftrees.secure.force.com/volunteers/">&nbsp\;Volunteer Page</a></b>\, 
 select the shift you will commit to\, &amp\; complete the waiver per the in
 structions provided.</b></li></ul><b></b><br>Thank you so much! We are so h
 appy to be working with you and doing our best to make this work. Your coop
 eration is critical to allowing us to host more events throughout the seaso
 n.
LAST-MODIFIED:20200812T214327Z
LOCATION:Location Provided upon Registration
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Tualatin "DIY" Mulching - Multiple Shifts\, Registration Required (
 Brown's Ferry Park) 
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
