DESCRIPTION:As part of the Rock Creek Partnership\, Friends of Trees is lea
 ding volunteer restoration events along the banks of Rock Creek. Rock Creek
  is a tributary to the Clackamas River and supports numerous species of wil
 dlife\, including salmonids.  This is our second year planting with the Bel
 la Casa Homeowners Association.\n\nWe provide breakfast snacks and hot choc
 olate/coffee for those who arrive at the planting before 9:00 am. We also p
 rovide tools\, gloves\, and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather a
 nd wearing boots or sturdy shoes and join us to plant trees!\n\n*This event
  is affiliated with the Alliance for Community Trees NeighborWoodsâ¢ Month
  and the Portland Timbers Stand Together Week.\n\nHeld in partnership with 
 Clackamas County Water Environmental Services.\n\n
