DESCRIPTION:Crew Leaders are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting
  trees properly and lead groups of volunteers at more than 80 different pla
 nting events during a planting season.  Friends of Trees is aiming to plant
  tens of thousands of native trees and shrubs at more than 40 public planti
 ng events in the Green Space Program.  Help us make those goals a reality a
 nd register to become a crew leader with us!  Crew Leaders commit to guidin
 g small groups of planters at 3-4 Saturday morning plantings. \n\n<b>This t
 raining is now full and closed to  further sign-ups.</b>  Thank you for you
 r interest!  Our next Crew Leader trainings will be held in Fall 2016.  If 
 you'd like to be added to a list to be contacted as soon as registration fo
 r our Fall trainings open\, please let us know at Volunteer@FriendsofTrees.
 org or 503-595-0213.\n
