DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrub
 s that were planted this past winter at this poplar gem of a park! We may a
 lso take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there 
 will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding w
 ork</u> (great for folks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events 
 help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summ
 er months ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>How do I register? </b><b> == </b>O
 nlin<u></u><u></u>e registration has closed at this time\, but there is sti
 ll room at this event\, please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.<
 b>==</b></p><p><b>Please arrive by 8:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\
 , stewardship activities start promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tool
 s\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and
  wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be re
 ady to have fun!<br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 an
 d under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer
  on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees
 .org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u>
 </u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  <
 /b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 r-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></
 b></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach u
 s at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u
 ><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u><
 /u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><hr /
 ><p>This event is in partnership with Clackamas Water Environment Services.
 </p>
