DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Due to popular support\, this event
  is <u>full and closed</u>.</b> Please consider any of our other open event
 s - we hope to work with you soon!</p><p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Join Frie
 nds of Trees and Clean Water Services at the Tualatin River Farm to improve
  the natural area through stewardship activities\, including making native 
 seed bombs\, weed removal\, and propagating native plants from seed and cut
 tings!</b> Please note: there will be no planting at this event. Tualatin R
 iver Farm is the headquarters for the Clean Water Services plant materials 
 team as they coordinate procuring\, storing\, and distributing more than 75
 0\,000 plants every year used in District revegetation projects. In additio
 n to providing some of the million plus native plants installed each year\,
  it functions as a working farm\, a nursery\, and a demonstration site for 
 innovative restoration techniques. </p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-i
 n and be assigned a crew. The event starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, t
 ools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/h
 ot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather weari
 ng sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?
