DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Help is needed to plant hundreds of native plants at our 
 King's Bend Natural Area Site! </b>Thank you for considering signing-up -- 
 this event *would not be possible* without community support!<br></p><p>Ple
 ase arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planti
 ng starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as
  well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to d
 o is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be
  ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration ha
 s closed\, but there is still room at this event!  Please simply show up an
 d sign-in at the registration table. Groups and individuals welcome!</p><p>
 <b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a pa
 rent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need
  to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth w
 aiver form</u></b></a> signed by their parent/guardian.<span> </span></p><p
 ><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u><
 /a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b>
 </u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><
 hr /><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with Clean Water Services\,
  Metro and City of Cornelius. This planting is part of Tree For All\, <span
 >a partnership which has planted more than ten million native plants in the
  Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Tre
 es\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and priv
 ate landowners will be working together this season to continue the success
  of this program. </span><br></p>
