DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><b>Celebrate Earth Day with Friends of Trees!
 </b> The goal of this event is to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs
  that were recently planted at this popular Happy Valley park. We may also 
 take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>Note: ther
 e will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demanding
  work</u>&nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tree 
 Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the 
 PNW dry summer months ahead.</html-blob><br><html-blob><u></u><p><b>How do 
 I register? </b>Online registration is closed at this time\, but there are 
 more spots available. Feel free to simply show up at 8:45am and sign-in whe
 n you arrive! Individuals and groups welcome!</p><p><b>Please arrive by 8:4
 5am</b>&nbsp\;to find our tent and sign-in\, and walk 10 minutes to the loc
 ation in the park we'll be working. Tree Care activities start promptly at 
 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is
  show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sand
 als of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>Under age
  18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/g
 uardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need
  to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">you
 th waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What
  about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number
  one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our 
 events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible
 \, such as children younger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a face ma
 sk through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance from ot
 hers not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any other
  snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your household
  feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a href=
 "https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently Asked Q
 uestions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nb
 sp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\
 ;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpa
 ge</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach G
 abriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftree
 s.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to wor
 king together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership with 
 and supported by the City of Happy Valley.</p><p><i>Friends of Trees contin
 ues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon
  Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, 
 we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.</i></
 p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
