DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Your he
 lp is needed to help plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs at McKay Sch
 ool Park in NE Salem! </b>In partnership with the City of Salem\, Friends o
 f Trees is undertaking a multi-year effort at McKay to help reduce weedy ve
 getation and establish a tree canopy to provide more shade and wildlife hab
 itat within the wetland area of the park. Without your help\, this event wo
 uldn't be possible -- thank you for considering signing-up!<u></u><br><br><
 u></u>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. T
 he planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guid
 ance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you 
 need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots
 \, and be ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register? </b>Pre-registrat
 ion for this event has now closed. There are still some spots available if 
 you'd like to show up!<br><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that you
 th 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older
  can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href=
 "http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></
 u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>What
  about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require</u>&nbsp\;that all people at
  our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to someon
 e who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\; We&nb
 sp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-vaccinated\, bring and wear a 
 face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 6’ of physical dista
 nce. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunte
 er-faq/"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></
 u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&n
 bsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><u
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer 
 FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to a
 ssist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailt
 o:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u
 ></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<
 /p><b><hr></b><p>This project is in partnership with the City of Salem.</p>
