DESCRIPTION:This Planting is part of the Tree for All event and is in conju
 nction with the city of Beaverton and Clean Water Services. We will be plan
 ting live stakes and bare root shrubs\, restoring the riparian area along S
 ummer Creek. The ambitious goal of Tree for All is to plant two million tre
 es in the Tualatin River Valley in 20 years. Friends of Trees will provide 
 morning refreshments\, gloves\, tools\, and all necessary guidance. NOTE: T
 his area can be very wet\, please wear waterproof boots and dress for the w
 eather. Please contact Andy Meeks at AndyM@FriendsofTrees.org or 503-282-88
 46 x24 for more information.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T154537Z
