 emove invasive English ivy from Tranquil Park.  The City used goats this pa
 st Fall to help remove large portions of the ivy and now it's our turn!  \n
 \nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The 
 event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot ch
 ocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dresse
 d for the weather and wearing sturdy\, <b>closed-toe shoes</b> (for your sa
 fety\, no sandals of any kind\, please!)\, and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b
 >Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups
  of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteeri
 ng/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individ
 uals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nPlease contact o
 ur Volunteer & Outreach Team at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or
  need more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!\n\n\n<b>Sp
 ecial thanks to Portland General Electric for generously sponsoring this ev
 ent.</b>
