DESCRIPTION:Memorial Park is 126 acres and Wilsonville's largest park. We w
 ill be meeting near the covered picnic shelters on the south east side of t
 he baseball and soccer fields. We will be planting native trees and shrubs 
 as well as removing ivy and other invasive plants from the area. \n\nThis p
 roject is supported by the City of Wilsonville.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:4
 5am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start prompt
 ly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as wel
 l as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and w
 earing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requeste
 d for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftree
 s.org/volunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.   Please
  contact Andy or Jenny at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need 
 more information. \n
LAST-MODIFIED:20190808T154537Z
LOCATION:Memorial City Park\, Wilsonville\, OR 97070
