DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/
 crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u>Planting C</u></a><a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u>rew
  Leaders</u></a> are trained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees a
 nd leading small group at our community planting events. Friends of Trees c
 annot run these events without the support of this valued position!  After 
 your training\, we expect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning eve
 nts Oct-May (select for events that fit your schedule!).    <br><br><u>This
  is the In-Person training for new Crew Leaders in the Green Space program.
   Please note: trainees will need to have completed the online training bef
 ore they attend this session</u>.  The online session will be sent to you a
 nd available for two weeks.<br><br>==================<br><b><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/crew-leader-training/" target="_blank">Register here</
 a></b> to save your place at this training.  Space limited.<br>============
 ======<br><br>Trainees can expect to plant different root stocks\, learn ab
 out tree identification\, hone your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet 
 the staff you'll be working alongside!<br><br>Questions? Please visit the <
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/"
  target="_blank"><u>Planting Crew Leader webpage</u></a> or contact: <a hre
 f="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u>volunteer@friend
 softrees.org</u></a>\, 503-595-0-213  We hope to work with you in this impo
 rtant role!
