DESCRIPTION:<b>Village Green Park Stewardship + Plant Giveaway - Earth Day 
 event</b><br><br>Celebrate Earth Day by mulching hundreds of native trees a
 nd shrubs that were planted this past winter. We may also take out some wee
 dy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-plant
 ing at this event\, and this is physically-demanding work</u> (great for fo
 lks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardship events help to ensure the hi
 ghest level of plant survival through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><
 br>This event is happening in tandem with a FOT free native tree and shrub 
 giveaway at Village Green Park (made possible by funding from State Farm an
 d the Arbor Day Foundation) from 10:00 am - 12:30 pm (or as supplies last).
  Volunteers are eligible to receive up to 4 native trees and/or shrubs (per
  household). This giveaway is focused on volunteers and Clackamas County re
 sidents\, though all are welcome. Trees and shrubs will be available on a f
 irst-come\, first-served basis. Volunteers that arrive early (between 8:30-
 8:45am) can request that we hold plants for them to pick up post-stewardshi
 p event. <u></u><p><b>How do I register? </b>Onlin<u></u><u></u><u></u>e re
 gistration has closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event\
 , please simply <u>show up at 8:45am</u> and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p
 ><b>Please arrive by 8:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in\, stewardship 
 activities start promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidan
 ce. All you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturd
 y shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fu
 n!<br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunt
 eer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own 
 and will need to hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiv
 er" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u>
 </u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  <
 /b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 r-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to as
 sist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_b
 lank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or<u></
 u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting
  together soon!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https:
 //laughingplanet.com/" target="_blank"><u><u>Laughing Planet</u></u></a>.</
 p><p>===</p><hr /><p>This event is in partnership with City of Happy Valley
 .</p><p><br></p>
