DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to mulch trees and shrubs at McKay School P
 ark!&nbsp\; This event is supported by the City of Salem.&nbsp\;<u>Note: th
 ere will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-demandi
 ng work</u>&nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\; Our Tre
 e Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through th
 e PNW dry summer months ahead.<br><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The
  safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Tr
 ees. We are requiring that all people at our events bring and wear a fabric
  face mask\, respect 6' or more of distance from others not in their own ho
 usehold\, and follow a few other protocols\, outlined on our&nbsp\;<b><a hr
 ef="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequently-Asked-Q
 uestions webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\;<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We reque
 st that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to include their paren
 t/guardian's contact information when they register online.<br><br><b>Quest
 ions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our tea
 m is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey a
 t&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org">volunteer@friendsoftr
 ees.org</a>&nbsp\;We look forward to seeing you out there!<br><br><i>Friend
 s of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by t
 he CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not safe 
 to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pre-
 registered.</i>
