CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:Despite some winter weather this week\, this planting is contin
 uing as planned -- please join us!<br><br>Join Friends of Trees and the Cit
 y of Salem for the second of this yearâs three planting events at the new
 ly opened Minto Island Conservation Area across the Minto Island Bridge! We
  will be planting native trees and shrubs along the new multi-use path conn
 ecting Riverfront Park with the greater Minto Brown Island Park. This event
  is partially funded with grants from Oregon Watershed Enhancement Board an
 d Meyer Memorial Trust.<br><br>Volunteer parking will be at Riverfront City
  Park.  You're welcome to park in the Carousel parking lot or the larger lo
 t along Water Street.  Either way there will be a short 5-10 min walk acros
 s the newly opened bridge to where we'll be planting.  Please arrive around
  8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promp
 tly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as we
 ll as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and 
 wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! <br><br><b>Loo
 king to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of 
 more than 5 people - click <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F
 %2Ffriendsoftrees.org%2Fvolunteering%2Fgroup-registration&amp\;sa=D&amp\;us
 t=1519341076308000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNG8OhGsRQhnH1qr3nVK_1nu7pLjPg" target="_bl
 ank">HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of
  4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!<br><br>Are you under age 18 and plan
 ting without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href="https://www.google.co
 m/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.friendsoftrees.org%2Fimages%2Fstories%2Fpdf%2FYout
 h_Waiver_2015.pdf&amp\;sa=D&amp\;ust=1519341076308000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNGsFBEY
 -EsKZudbP6iCDCycfVMKcQ" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for yo
 u to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanie
 d by an adult.<br><br>Please contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if yo
 u have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing yo
 u out in Salem!<br><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor\, <a href="htt
 ps://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2F%2F&amp\;sa=D&amp\;us
 t=1519341076308000&amp\;usg=AFQjCNGJmQo4rZDw_dL1ozbUQ5kG7vk-HQ" target="_bl
 ank">REI</a>!<br>===
