DESCRIPTION:This event is in partnership with the City of Tualatin and Clea
 n Water Services. We will be planting hundreds of native trees and shrubs a
 t Brown's Ferry Park. This planting is part of the Tree For All campaign wh
 ich has planted over three million native plants in the Tualatin River Wate
 rshed in the past decade! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousan
 ds of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowne
 rs will be working together this season to continue the success of this pro
 gram.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a cre
 w. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and
  hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come
  dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun
 !\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for
  groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/vol
 unteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for 
 individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nPlease co
 ntact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need mo
 re information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
