CREATED:20230831T134610Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>========</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this even
 t is <u>full and closed</u>.</b>  Please consider any of our other upcoming
  open events - we hope to plant with you soon!</p><p><b>========</b></p><p>
 <b>Help needed to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs at this special
  arboretum\, often referred to as  </b><span><b>one of NE Portland's "hidde
 n gems."</b> </span><span>We will be planting and removing invasive species
  including Himalayan Blackberry and English Ivy.</span><br></p><p><span>*Pl
 ease note this event starts 1 hour later than most of our plantings. </span
 ><u>Please arrive by 9:45am</u><span> to sign-in and be assigned a planting
  crew. The planting starts at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and plan
 ting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate --
  all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes
  or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</span><br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>
 <span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.
   Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a 
 </span><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver f
 orm</u></b></a><span> signed by their parent/guardian.</span><br></p><p><b>
 Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vo
 lunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></
 u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</
 u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></
 p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with <span>Portla
 nd OIC\, Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation\, the Columbia Slough Watershed C
 ouncil\, and Friends of the Columbia Children's Arboretum.</span></p>
