 r consideration!<br><br>****************<br>Join us as we mulch hundreds of
  native trees and shrubs that were planted this past winter!&nbsp\; We may 
 also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\; Our Tre
 e Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through ou
 r dry summer months.<br><br>Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered an
 d assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide b
 reakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and gu
 idance. Please come dressed for the weather\, wear sturdy shoes (no sandals
  of any kind\, please!)--and get ready to have fun!<br><br><b><u>Under age 
 18? </u></b>A signed <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/
 Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you
  to volunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an
