DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and the City of Salem for the final plant
 ing event at the Minto Island Conservation Area. Help put the finishing tou
 ches on the planting project along the new multi-use path connecting Riverf
 ront Park with the greater Minto Brown Island Park -- many hundreds of nati
 ve trees and plants await your assistance to be in their forever homes! Thi
 s event is partially funded with grants from Oregon Watershed Enhancement B
 oard and Meyer Memorial Trust.<br><br><i>Please note: Volunteer parking wil
 l be at Riverfront City Park at the above address. You're welcome to park i
 n the Carousel parking lot (which is closest) or the larger lot along Water
  Street. Either way\, please plan for a 5-10 min walk across the bridge to 
 where we'll be planting.&nbsp\; Look for the "Friends of Trees" signs to gu
 ide you!</i><br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some break
 fast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. The planting starts prompt
 ly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to
  do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots â
  and be ready to have fun! <br><br><b>How do I register?</b>&nbsp\;Online 
 registration closes 24 hours before the planting begins\, but there is stil
 l room at this event -- please simply show up!<br><br><b>Under age 18?</b> 
 A signed <b><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Wai
 ver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth waiver</a></b> is required for you to v
 olunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adul
 t.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a 
 href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friend
 softrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any further information. We 
 look forward to seeing you out there!<br><br>===<br>Thank you to our event 
 sponsors\, <a href="https://www.rei.com/" target="_blank">REI</a>&nbsp\;and
  <a href="https://www.portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank">PGE</a>.<br>===
 &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;
