CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive 8:30-8:45am to be registered and assigned to a cr
 ew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks
  and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please 
 come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have
  fun! Project parking is available at the 24 Hour Fitness parking lot\; ple
 ase refrain from taking parking spots near the entrance of the 24 Hour. Fol
 low event signs from there to the planting site.\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer
  as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 peopl
 e - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration
 >HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for groups of 4 or less.\n\n<i>T
 his planting is part of the Tree For All campaign which strives to plant on
 e million native trees and shrubs during the 2014-2015 planting season with
 in the Tualatin River Watershed.  Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\,
  the Tualatin River Watershed Council\, thousands of volunteers\, other non
 -profits\, City partners\, and private landowners will all be working toget
 her to make this happen!\n\nBeaverton's Mayor Doyle and other community par
 tners will also be in attendance.  Arrive as early as 8:30am to meet these 
 Tree for All partners\, partake of refreshments and enter to win a commemor
 ative Tree for All cap\, courtesy of David Evans & Associates.</i>\n\nPleas
 e contact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need 
 more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
