DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and the City of Lake Oswego in planting n
 ative trees\, shrubs\, and herbaceous plants to help restore this important
  habitat area adjacent to the Tualatin River. This project is part of a lar
 ger effort under way by the City of Lake Oswego in partnership with Ash Cre
 ek Forestry to improve over 65 acres of regionally significant ecological c
 ommunities in the immediate area.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be regi
 stered and assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We 
 provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, too
 ls and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, c
 losed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a 
 group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - cl
 ick <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE<
 /a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewe
 r -- you can simply show up!\n\nAre you under age 18 and planting without y
 our parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/images
 /stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required for you to 
 volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by 
 an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have an
 y questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing you out the
 re!\n\n<i>Accessible on Bus Line 36.  For more directions\, visit <a href=h
 ttps://trimet.org/>https://trimet.org/</a>.</i>\n\n===\nThank you to our ev
 ent sponsor\, <a href=https://www.bartlett.com/>Bartlett Tree Experts</a>!\
 n===
