DESCRIPTION:<p>Join Friends of Trees and the City of Happy Valley as we pla
 nt hundreds of pollinator-friendly native plants creating a pollinator gard
 en at Village Green Park! These plants will help create valuable habitat fo
 r native pollinators and provide seasonal beauty for park go-ers. </p><p>Pl
 ease arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plant
 ing starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, a
 s well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to 
 do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and b
 e ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>How do I register? </b>Pre-Registration i
 s now closed but planters are still needed\, just simply show up :)</p><p><
 b>Parking Note:</b> Street parking encouraged on Hines Drive and the surrou
 nding neighborhood. </p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 an
 d under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer
  on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftre
 es.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u>
 </u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>
 Transit: </b>B<span>us Line 155 with a .2 mile walk.</span></p><p><b>Questi
 ons?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/vo
 lunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></
 u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can
  reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" targ
 et="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></
 u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together so
 on!</p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://portlandge
 neral.com/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u><
 /a>.</p><p>===</p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership w
 ith the City of Happy Valley.</p>
