  or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!<p><b
 >Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a pare
 nt/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need t
 o hand us a <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><u><u
 ><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/gu
 ardian.</p><p><b>What about event safety?</b> Friends of Trees <u>re<u></u>
 quires</u> that all people at our events cancel if you feel unwell or have 
 been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of t
 he event.  See our safety recommendations and more on the <b><u><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></u></u
 ></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.              </p><p><b>Quest
 ions?  </b>Please check out our <b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></u></a></b
 >.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Gabriel and Jenny at <
 a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u><u><b>volunteer@fr
 iendsoftrees.org</b></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to working tog
 ether soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sponsors <a href="https
 ://portlandgeneral.com/"><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></a> &amp\;
  <a href="https://laughingplanet.com/">Laughing Planet</a>.<br>===<br></p><
 b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with City of Salem.</p>
