DESCRIPTION:=============<br><br>Due to popular interest\, this event is no
 w <b><u>full and closed</u></b>.&nbsp\; Please consider any of our other op
 en planting events\, including returning to Jackson Bottom on Sat Oct 9th a
 nd Sat Oct 23rd!<br><br><br>=============<br>Your help is needed to plant h
 undreds of native trees and shrubs at the first planting of the planting se
 ason. Let's kick-off the season together by making a difference at the beau
 tiful Jackson Bottom Wetlands wildlife preserve!<br><br>Please arrive by 8:
 45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:0
 0am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need to d
 o is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be
  ready to have fun! <br><br><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that yout
 h 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian<u></u>.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b> signed by t
 heir parent/guardian.<br><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety o
 f volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We a
 re requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the e
 xception of those younger than 12 and anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromis
 ed and not eligible for the vaccine)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a fabric
  face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance
  from others not in their own household\, bring&nbsp\;your own water bottle
  and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in 
 your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&
 nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer Frequen
 tly Aske<u></u>d Questions webpage</a>&nbsp\;for more details.<br><br><b>Qu
 estion<u></u>s?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="htt
 ps://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp
 \; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Jenny and Carey a
 t&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@fr<u></u
 >iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward to planting together
  soon!<br><br><b><hr><p></p></b>This event is in partnership with the City 
 of Hillsboro and Clean Water Services at Jackson Bottom Wetlands preserve\,
  an amazing wildlife preserve. This planting is part of Tree For All\, a pa
 rtnership which has planted more than ten million native plants in the Tual
 atin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, 
 thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private l
 andowners will be working together this season to continue the success of t
 his program.&nbsp\;<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guid
 elines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If 
 at any point we feel it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them an
 d notify any volunteers who are pre-registered.<u></u></i>
