 >&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Fr
 iends of Trees. We are requiring that all people at our events are fully-va
 ccinated (with the exception of those who are ineligible\, such as children
  younger than 5\, anyone&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&n
 bsp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6
 ' or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your o
 wn water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cance
 l if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. 
 Please see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b
 >Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more detail
 s.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<
 /b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to a
 ssist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="m
 ailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>
 &nbsp\;We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr><br></b>Thi
 s planting is in partnership with the City of Forest Grove and Clean Water 
 Services\, and part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more 
 than ten million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005.<
 br><br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommend
 ations made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel
  it is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunte
 ers who are pre-registered.</i></html-blob>
