DESCRIPTION:In partnership with Portland Parks & Recreation\, the Johnson C
 reek Watershed Council\, and East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation Distr
 ict we will be removing invasive plants from one of our earlier native tree
  and shrub planting areas along the Springwater Corridor Trail.\n\nPlease a
 rrive by 8:45am and we'll provide coffee and doughnuts to get your started.
  We'll also provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do i
 s show up dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and we'll assign
  you to a planting team led by one of our trained Crew Leaders. \n\nRSVPs a
 re kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http:/
 /www.friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> 
 to do so.   \n\nPlease contact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have a
 ny questions or need more information. \n\n<i>This event is generously spon
 sored by Portland General Electric.</i>
