CREATED:20190808T153337Z
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive 8:30-8:45am to be registered and assigned to a cr
 ew. Due to extremely limited parking at the planting site\, there will be a
  short shuttle ride from the church to the site (and back).  The planting w
 ill start at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\,
  as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weathe
 r and wearing sturdy shoes (rubber boots work great) and get ready to have 
 fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested
  for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org
 /volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required 
 for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nAs pa
 rt of the Rock Creek Partnership with SOLVE and the Clackamas River Basin C
 ouncil\, Friends of Trees is leading volunteer restoration events along the
  banks of Rock Creek and its tributaries. Rock Creek is a tributary to the 
 Clackamas River and supports numerous species of wildlife\, including salmo
 nids. This project is supported with funding from Clackamas County Water En
 vironment Services\, on behalf of Clackamas Service District No. 1. \n\nPle
 ase contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or n
 eed more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
