DESCRIPTION:Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrub
 s that were planted this past winter at this 2-acre parcel of land along th
 e Columbia Slough! We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if t
 ime allows. <u>Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and thi
 s is physically-demanding work</u> (great for folks looking for a work out!
 ).  Our stewardship events help to ensure the highest level of plant surviv
 al through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>How do I
  register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, but this event
  still has space! Please simply show-up at 9:45am and sign-in at the welcom
 e table. Hope to see you there!</p><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to fin
 d our tent and sign-in\, stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00am. 
 We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dre
 ssed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any k
 ind\, please!) and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><a href="ht
 tps://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u>youth 
 waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></a></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p
 ><p><b>Transit:</b> B<span>us Line 87 with a .2 mile walk.</span></p><p></p
 ><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl<u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volu
 nteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is als
 o happy to assist!  Reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@frien
 dsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></
 u>iendsoftrees.or<u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look f
 orward to working together soon!<br></p><p>===<br>Thank you to our event sp
 onsor <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" target="_blank"><u><u>Portland
  General Electric</u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><hr /><p>This event is in partn
 ership with Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation\, Portland OIC\, and <span>7 W
 aters Canoe Family.</span></p>
