 ins are a concern\,&nbsp\;vaccination rates in Oregon are low\, and Multnom
 ah County is considered&nbsp\;<a href="https://coronavirus.oregon.gov/Pages
 /living-with-covid-19.aspx">"Ext<u></u>reme Risk" by the State of Oregon</a
 >.&nbsp\; For all these reasons\, we feel it is irresponsible to gather a g
 roup of people\, even outdoors with proper safety protocol.&nbsp\;<br><br>=
 ====<u></u>============&nbsp\;&nbsp\;<br><span><span>&nbsp\;</span></span><
 br><span><span></span></span>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with Po
 rtland OIC and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation with support from the East 
 Multnomah Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District and Metro to help restore
  this important natural area.<br><br><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The 
