DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees and the City of Salem for the second of t
 his yearâs three planting events at the Minto Island Conservation Area. W
 e will be planting native trees and shrubs along the new multi-use path con
 necting Riverfront Park with the greater Minto Brown Island Park. This even
 t is partially funded with grants from Oregon Watershed Enhancement Board a
 nd Meyer Memorial Trust.<br><br><i>Please note: Volunteer parking will be a
 t Riverfront City Park at the above address. You're welcome to park in the 
 Carousel parking lot (which is closest) or the larger lot along Water Stree
 t. Either way\, please plan for a 5-10 min walk across the bridge to where 
 we'll be planting.  Look for the "Friends of Trees" signs to guide you!</i>
 <br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats 
