DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><b><br><hr><p></p></b><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/salem/">Planting Crew Leaders</a> are trained volunteers who a
 re crucial to planting trees and leading small group at Friends of Trees co
 mmunity planting events. We can not run these events without the support of
  this valued position! This training is for our mid-Valley Salem planting e
 vents where you'll plant both small-stock (gallon container or smaller) nat
 ive trees and shrubs in an ecological-rest<u></u>oration style\, as well as
  large-stock (8-12' trees) in local parks and neighborhoods.<br><br><b><a h
 ref="https://friendsoftrees.org/salem/"><u>Learn more and register here</u>
 </a></b>&nbsp\;for this important position. <u>Space limited\, but there is
  still space available and we welcome new registrants until Fri\, 10/28</u>
 .<br><u></u><ul><li><u></u><b><u>A note on planting location and personal t
 ransportation</u>:<u></u></b>&nbsp\;You will be eligible to Crew Lead at al
 l eight Salem events\, as well as in other cities in the Portland-Metro are
 a if you choose. Personal transportation is recommended-- there may be time
 s carpools are available\, but this is not guaranteed since it depends on t
 he comfort of other FOT volunteers.<u></u></li><li><b><u>What about Covid-1
 9?</u></b>&nbsp\; Friends of Trees&nbsp\;<u>requires</u>&nbsp\;that all peo
 ple at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or have been exposed to 
 someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 days of the event.&nbsp\;
  We&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>every<u></u>one is fully-vaccinate<u></u>d
 \, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and respect 
 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions web
 page</u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.</li></ul><b><p></p><hr><p>
 </p></b>Ple<u></u>a<u></u>se contact Jenny or Gabriel if you need more info
 rmation or have questions:&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.o
 rg"><u>volu<u></u>nteer@frien<u></u>dsof<u></u>trees.org</u></a>. We look f
 orward to working with you this planting season!<u></u></html-blob>
