DESCRIPTION:===============================================================
 ==\n\n<b>Due to popular interest\, this planting is now full and closed to 
 further groups.</b> We encourage you to sign-up for a different event we ha
 ve!  RSVPs are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you 
 may simply show up!\n\n====================================================
 =============\n\nJoin us for the final of three plantings to improve habita
 t for pollinators!  Volunteers need to park off of  SW Schroeder Way near t
 he Community Garden.  Parking will be limited\, so we strongly encourage ca
 r pooling to the event! \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered an
 d assigned to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide b
 reakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and gu
 idance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe
  shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nThese plantings are all part of the Be
 e Stewards Wilsonville project in partnership with the City of Wilsonville\
 ; Northwest Center for Alternatives to Pesticides\; The West Linn Wilsonvil
 le School District\, Center for Research in Environmental Sciences and Tech
 nology\; Xerces Society for Invertebrate Conservation\; Northwest Youth Cor
 ps\; Habitat Landscape Design\; Oregon State University North Willamette Re
 search and Extension among others. This project is supported by Metro and t
 he National Fish and Wildlife Foundation.\n\nPlease contact Jenny at (503) 
 595-0213 if you have questions or need any further information.\n\nWe look 
 forward to seeing you out there!\n\n<b>Thank you to PGE for generously spon
 soring this planting!<b>\n\n
