DESCRIPTION:Join us at Tranquil Park on this special Monday planting to hel
 p celebrate the Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Day of Service!  Friends of Tree
 s is excited to continue our partnership this season with the City of WIlso
 nville.  We will be planting native trees and shrubs as well as removing En
 glish ivy.  \n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned t
 o a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast 
 snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. P
 lease come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes an
 d get ready to have fun! \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs 
 are kindly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSV
 Ps are not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simp
 ly show up!\n\nAre you under age 18 and planting without your parent/guardi
 an?  A signed <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Yout
 h_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We kin
 dly request youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.\n\nPlea
 se contact Jenny or Pablo at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or ne
 ed more information. We look forward to celebrating Dr. King's legacy of se
 rvice by planting trees together!
