DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer
 /how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Planting C</a><a href="https://friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">rew Leaders</a>&nbsp\;are t
 rained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading small group
  at our community planting events. Friends of Trees can not run these event
 s without the support of this valued position!<br><br><u>This is the hands-
 on training for new Crew Leaders in the Green Space program.&nbsp\; Please 
 note: trainees will need to have completed the online training before they 
 attend this hands-on session</u>.&nbsp\; Trainees can expect to plant diffe
 rent root stocks\, learn about tree identification\, and meet other Crew Le
 aders and staff!<br><br><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/ho
 w-to-volunteer/crew-leader/">Register for this online and hands-on training
  today</a>!</b><u></u><br><br><u></u>Following the training we will ask you
  to sign-up to help lead crews at 3+ planting events through the end of May
  '23.&nbsp\; This is a great role for those looking to continue their tree 
 and/or inclusive leadership education!<u></u></html-blob>
