DESCRIPTION:Join Friends of Trees at the second of two plantings this seaso
 n at Jack City Park!\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and as
 signed to a crew. The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide break
 fast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidan
 ce. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get re
 ady to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindl
 y requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friends
 oftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are no
 t required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show u
 p!\n\nThis event is in partnership with the City of Tigard and Clean Water 
 Services. This planting is part of the Tree For All campaign which has plan
 ted over three million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed in the
  past decade! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands of volunt
 eers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners will be w
 orking together this season to continue the success of this program.\n\nPle
 ase contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or n
 eed more information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
