 We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\;
  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to include the
 ir parent/guardian's contact information when they register online.<br><br>
 This planting is in partnership with the City of Tualatin and Clean Water s
 ervices\, and part of Tree For All\, a partnership which has planted more t
 han ten million native plants in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005.&n
 bsp\;&nbsp\;<b><br></b><br><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out 
 our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer 
 FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You ca
 n reach Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friend
 softrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward
  to seeing you out there!&nbsp\; &nbsp\;<br><br><i>Friends of Trees continu
 es to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by the CDC and Oregon 
