DESCRIPTION:<p><b>====================</b></p><p><b>This event is now full 
 and closed</b>. Please consider our second Jackson Bottom event the followi
 ng weekend on Saturday\, Oct 11th. <b></b></p><p><b>=====================</
 b></p><p><b>Help us kick-off the 25-26 planting season at Jackson Bottom We
 tlands Preserve! </b>You help needed to plant hundreds of native plants in 
 the wetlands\, a 635-acre wetland complex on the Tualatin River that is des
 ignated as an 'Important Bird Area' for both migrating and nonmigratory spe
 cies.</p><p>Please arrive by 8:45amto sign-in and be assigned a planting cr
 ew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting
  guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all
  you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or 
 boots\, and be ready to have fun!</p><p><i>**Please note: there is a 10 min
 ute walk from the parking area to where we'll be planting. Please plan your
  timing accordingly.</i></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 1
 5 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volun
 teer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendso
 ftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank">youth waiver form</a></u></b> signe
 d by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <
 b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank">Vo
 lunteer FAQ webpage</a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You ca
 n reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" tar
 get="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forwa
 rd to planting together soon!</p><p>===</p><p>Thank you to our event sponso
 r\, <a href="https://epson.com/hillsboro" target="_blank">Epson Portland\, 
 Inc.</a></p><p>===</p><p><b><br></b></p><p><br></p><b><hr /></b><p><br>This
  event is in partnership with the City of Hillsboro.</p>
