DESCRIPTION:Join us in partnership with North Clackamas Urban Watershed Cou
 ncil to plant native trees and shrubs along Mount Scott Creek! This plantin
 g is possible with the support of Clackamas County Service District #1.\n\n
 Meet us around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The event wi
 ll start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/
 coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for th
 e weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get ready to have fun! 
 \n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly requested for 
 groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://friendsoftrees.org/volu
 nteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not required for i
 ndividuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply show up!\n\nAre you un
 der age 18 and planting without your parent/guardian?  A signed <a href=htt
 p://www.friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf>youth w
 aiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We kindly request youth 15 year
 s and younger are accompanied by an adult.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Pablo
  at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We l
 ook forward to seeing you in Happy Valley!\n\n<i>Accessible on Bus Line 155
 .  For more directions\, visit <a href=https://trimet.org/>https://trimet.o
 rg/</a>.</i>
