DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><br>====<br>&nbsp\;</html-blob><br><html-blob
 >Pre-registration for this event is now closed\, BUT **we still have some l
 ast-minute spots available**. Feel free to show up and sign the waiver on-s
 ite this Saturday!&nbsp\;</html-blob><br><html-blob>&nbsp\;</html-blob><br>
 <html-blob>For youth under 18 (volunteering w/out a parent or guardian)\, p
 lease make sure you bring a completed <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/y
 outhwaiver" id="ow745" __is_owner="true">Youth Waiver</a>.<br><br>====<u></
 u><br><u></u><u></u>Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees a
 nd shrubs that were planted this past winter at this natural areas site! We
  may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows.&nbsp\;<u>
 Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically
 -demanding work</u>&nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work out!).&nbsp\;
  Our Tree Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival th
 rough the PNW dry summer months ahead. Were proud of this event being part 
 of the <b>Greening Wilkes </b>collaboration\, please see more info below.<u
 ></u><br><u></u><p><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b>&nbsp\;to find our tent an
 d sign-in\, Tree Care activities start promptly at 10:00am. We provide glov
 es\, tools\, and guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for th
 e weather and wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, pleas
 e!) and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We reque
 st that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b>
 <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" id="ow735" __is_owner="tru
 e">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><
 b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunteers and staff is our 
 number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requiring that all people a
 t our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception of those who are inel
 igible\, such as children younger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a f
 ace mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance f
 rom others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and any
  other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your hou
 sehold feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<a
  href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently A
 sked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp
 \; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out our
 &nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FAQ
  webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can r
 each Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friends
 oftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward 
 to working together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This event is in partnership
  with Portland OIC and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation with support from t
 he East Multnomah Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District and Portland Clea
 n Energy Fund.&nbsp\;</p><p>This event is part of a day-long celebration or
 ganized by Greening Wilkes. Greening Wilkes is a collaborative project to e
 ngage the community surrounding Wilkes Park and Wilkes Natural Area to enha
 nce and diversify green spaces throughout the neighborhood. Friends of Tree
 s\, Verde\, Columbia Slough Watershed Council and Portland Audubon have tea
 med up together to lead complementary events and outings for the local comm
 unity to help in this habitat enhancement effort\, learn about the amazing 
 natural resources that are present\, and help envision how the open spaces 
 may add resilience and health to the community in the future.</p><p><i>Frie
 nds of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendations made by
  the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it is not saf
 e to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers who are pr
 e-registered.</i><br></p><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u></html-b
 lob>
