DESCRIPTION:=======<br><b>Registration for this training is now closed</b>.
  Please consider our Nov 1st or Nov 8th trainings with the Neighborhood Tre
 es program.<br><br>=======<br><b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunt
 eer/how-to-volunteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>Planting C</u><
 /u></u></a><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-volunteer/c
 rew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u>rew Leaders</u></u></u></a></b> are t
 rained volunteers who are crucial to planting trees and leading small group
  at our community planting events. Friends of Trees cannot run these events
  without the support of this valued position!  After your training\, we exp
 ect you to help lead a crew at 4 Saturday morning events Oct-April (select 
 for events that fit your schedule!).<br><br><u>This is an In-Person trainin
 g for new Crew Leaders in the Green Space program.  Please note: trainees w
 ill need to have completed the online training before they attend this sess
 ion</u>.  The online session will be emailed to you\, and you'll have two w
 eeks to complete it before this in-person training.<br><br>Trainees can exp
 ect to plant different root stocks\, learn about tree identification\, hone
  your inclusive leadership skills\, and meet the staff you'll be working al
 ongside! Lunch provided\, as well as a "Tree Team" tshirt!<br><br>Questions
 ? Please visit the <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer/how-to-vol
 unteer/crew-leader/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><b>Planting Crew Leader webpa
 ge</b></u></u></u></a> or contact: <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees
 .org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a>\, 503-595-0213  We l
 ook forward to working with you in this important role!
