DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Your help is needed to plant hundreds of native shrubs an
 d herbaceous plants at Wapato Lake National Wildlife Refuge!</b> This is on
 e of the nation's newest wildlife refuges\, consisting of 817 acres within 
 a 5\,000 acre network of near-contiguous publicly-owned natural areas conne
 cting wetlands\, floodplains\, and waterways. Thank you for considering joi
 ning this important planting effort!<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to s
 ign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We p
 rovide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks
  and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for 
 the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br><b
 r><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this time\, b
 ut there is still space at this event!  Please simply show up and sign-in w
 hen you arrive.</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and und
 er volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on t
 heir own and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/yout
 hwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a> signed by their parent/guardia
 n.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u><
 /u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailt
 o:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org
 </u></b></u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p>
 <p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This event is in partnership with <span>Clean Wa
 ter Services\, Tualatin River National Wildlife Refuge\, the Tualatin Valle
 y Irrigation District\, the Joint Water Commission\, and USFWS.</span></p>
