DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Your help is needed to help plant native trees and shrubs
  following the removal of the Balm Grove Dam a few miles Northwest of Fores
 t Grove. </b>This planting is in partnership with Clean Water Services\, wh
 o has been working with Tree for All partners to remove this dam and improv
 e fish passage in Gales Creek since 2016. Your support is crucial to the su
 ccess of this project -- thank you for considering signing-up!<br></p><p>Pl
 ease arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The plant
 ing starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, a
 s well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to 
 do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and b
 e ready to have fun!<br><br><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration h
 as closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event!  Please sim
 ply show up and sign-in when you arrive.</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <a href="http:
 //friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a> signe
 d by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunt
 eer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to ass
 ist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u
 ><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></a> We look for
 ward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><hr /><p></p><p><br>This even
 t is in partnership with Clean Water Services.</p>
