DESCRIPTION:<i>**Please note: this is a different location than "Stites Cit
 y Park."  Don't be confused by google maps\, which due to the new nature of
  this park erroneously places it 1 mile from the actual site we'll be plant
 ing at.  Find us at the above address.**</i><br><br>Join Friends of Trees\,
  Clean Water Services\, and the City of Forest Grove as we plant at the yet
 -unopened Helen Stites Park! These hundreds of native trees and shrubs need
  your help to be planted in their new home.<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am 
 to sign-in and enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocol
 ate. The planting starts promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, an
 d guidance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and w
 earing sturdy shoes or boots â and be ready to have fun! <br><b><br>How d
 o I register?</b>&nbsp\;Online registration closes the day before our event
 s\, but this planting is still open to volunteers -- please simply show up 
 at 8:45am!<br><br><b>Under age 18? </b>A signed <a href="http://friendsoftr
 ees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" target="_blank">youth wai
 ver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We ask that youth 15 years and yo
 unger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>This planting is part of Tree For
  All\, a partnership which has planted more than eight million native plant
 s in the Tualatin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friend
 s of Trees\, thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, 
 and private landowners will be working together this season to continue the
  success of this program.<br><br>Please contact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey a
 t (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_
 blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if you have questions or need any f
 urther information. We look forward to seeing you out there!
