DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u>==========<u></u><br><br><u></u><b>Due to pop
 ular interest\, this event is <u>full and closed</u></b>. Please consider a
 ny of our other available events -- thank you for your interest!<br><u></u>
 <br>==========<br><u></u><br><u></u><u></u>Come plant native trees and shru
 bs to help restore the Johnson Creek Watershed's native habitats and improv
 e water quality! This event is part of the Johnson Creek Watershed Wide Eve
 nt where lunch will be provided (yay lunch!).<p>Please arrive by 8:45am to 
 sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We 
 provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance -- all you need to do is sho
 w up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready t
 o have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and u
 nder volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunt
 eer on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://frien
 dsoftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their 
 parent/guardian.<br></p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of 
 volunteers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are
  requiring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exc
 eption of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5\, anyo
 ne&nbsp\;severely immunocompromised\, etc)<b>\,</b>&nbsp\;bring and wear a 
 face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6' or more of distance 
 from others not in their own household\, bring your own water bottle and an
 y other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel if anyone in your ho
 usehold feels unwell within two weeks of this event. Please see our&nbsp\;<
 a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>Volunteer Frequently 
 Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbs
 p\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Please check out ou
 r&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/">Volunteer FA
 Q webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can 
 reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="mailto:Volunteer@friend
 softrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&nbsp\;We look forward
  to planting together soon!<br></p><b><hr><br></b>This project is in partne
 rship with the Johnson Creek Watershed Council and Portland Parks &amp\; Re
 creation with support from Clackamas County Water Environment Services.<br>
 <br><i>Friends of Trees continues to follow the guidelines and recommendati
 ons made by the CDC and Oregon Health Authority. If at any point we feel it
  is not safe to host events\, we will cancel them and notify any volunteers
  who are pre-registered.</i><br><u></u><br>===<br>Thank you to our event sp
 onsors&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.hopworksbeer.com/">Hopworks Urban Brewery
 </a>&nbsp\;&amp\; <a href="https://treecology.com/">Treecology</a>!<br>===<
 i><br></i><u></u><u></u><br><u></u><u></u></html-blob>
