DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Due to popular interest\, this event
  is <u>full and closed</u>.  </b>We hope to plant with you at another event
  soon!</p><p><b>=======</b></p><p><b>Friends of Trees is excited to partner
  with Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation to help restore one of N Portland's 
 most treasured parks: Kelley Point Park.</b> We will be planting hundreds o
 f native trees and shrubs and are grateful for your support which makes thi
 s event possible!<br></p><p><span>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be
  assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves
 \, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/t
 ea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather w
 earing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!</span></p><p><b>Un
 der age 18?</b><span> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a p
 arent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will nee
 d to hand us a </span><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><b><u
 >youth waiver form</u></b></a><span> signed by their parent/guardian.</span
 ><br></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friend
 softrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></a>.  Our 
