DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><br>====<br><br>Due to popular interest this event i
 s now&nbsp\;<u><b>full and closed</b></u>.&nbsp\; We hope to work with you 
 next planting/tree care season -- events start again in Oct!<br><br>====<u>
 </u><br><u></u>Your help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and sh
 rubs that were planted this past winter at this gem of a park in inner NE P
 ortland! We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows
 .&nbsp\;<u>Note: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is
  physically-demanding work</u>&nbsp\;(great for folks looking for a work ou
 t!).&nbsp\; Our Tree Care events help to ensure the highest level of plant 
 survival through the PNW dry summer months ahead.<u></u><br><u></u><p><b>Pl
 ease arrive by 9:45am</b>&nbsp\;to find our tent and sign-in\, Tree Care ac
 tivities start promptly at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and guidanc
 e\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearing st
 urdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be ready to have
  fun!<br></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and und
 er volunteer with a parent/guardian.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can voluntee
 r on their own and will need to hand us a&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friends
 oftrees.org/youthwaiver">youth waiver form</a></b>&nbsp\;signed by their pa
 rent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;The safety of volunt
 eers and staff is our number one priority at Friends of Trees. We are requi
 ring that all people at our events are fully-vaccinated (with the exception
  of those who are ineligible\, such as children younger than 5)<b>\,</b>&nb
 sp\;bring and wear a face mask through the event introductions\, respect 6'
  or more of distance from others not in their own household\, bring your ow
 n water bottle and any other snacks or beverages you will need\, and cancel
  if anyone in your household feels unwell within two weeks of this event. P
 lease see our&nbsp\;<a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><b>
 Volunteer Frequently Asked Questions webpage</b></a>&nbsp\;for more details
 .&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</
 b>Please check out our&nbsp\;<b><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunte
 er-faq/">Volunteer FAQ webpage</a></b>.&nbsp\; Our team is also happy to as
 sist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel\, Carey\, and Jenny at&nbsp\;<a href="ma
 ilto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><b>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</b></a>&
 nbsp\;We look forward to working together soon!<br></p><b><hr></b><p>This e
 vent is in partnership with Portland OIC\, Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation
 \, the Columbia Slough Watershed Council\, and Friends of the Columbia Chil
