CREATED:20230830T194941Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Your help is needed to plant trees at the second planting
  this season at Jackson Bottom Wetlands Preserve\, an amazing haven for wil
 dlife. </b>Jackson Bottom is a 635-acre wetland complex on the Tualatin Riv
 er that is designated as an Important Bird Area for both migrating and non-
 migratory species. Please sign-up to help continue these important planting
  restoration efforts!<br></p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be a
 ssigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. <b><i>**Please note
  that there is a 10-15 min walk from the parking lot to the planting locati
 on\, please factor in the walk time so you can still arrive ~8:45am.</i></b
 >  We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast
  snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dress
 ed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun
 !<br><br><b>How do I register? </b>Online registration has closed at this t
 ime but there is still room at this event.  Please simply sign-in when you 
 arrive!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volun
 teer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own
  and will need to hand us a <a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"
 ><b><u>youth waiver form</u></b></a> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p
 ><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.or
 g/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></b></u></u></u><
 /a>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b>
 </u></u></u></a> We look forward to planting together soon!<br></p><p></p><
 hr /><p></p><p><span>This event is in partnership with Clean Water Services
  and the City of Hillsboro. This planting is part of Tree For All\, a partn
 ership which has planted more than ten million native plants in the Tualati
 n River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, tho
 usands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private land
 owners will be working together this season to continue the success of this
  program. </span></p>
