DESCRIPTION:Help revitalize Hall Creek in partnership with Comcast Cares Da
 y in the heart of Beaverton during Earth Month and Arbor Month! This event 
 is part of a broader creek restoration project being completed by the City 
 of Beaverton to improve water quality and beautify the area. We'll be mulch
 ing all recently planted trees and shrubs to prepare them for survival duri
 ng the warmer summer months.\n\nThanks to the generosity of Comcast\, there
  will be breakfast snacks and sandwich box lunches provided for all volunte
 ers!\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew
 . The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools and gu
 idance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, <b>closed-
 toe shoes</b> (for your safety\, no sandals of any kind\, please!)\, and ge
 t ready to have fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are k
 indly requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://fri
 endsoftrees.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs ar
 e not required for individuals or groups of 4 or fewer -- you can simply sh
 ow up!\n\nPlease contact our Volunteer & Outreach Team at (503) 595-0213 if
  you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seeing
  you out there!
