DESCRIPTION:<p>Join Friends of Trees to plant hundreds of native trees and 
 shrubs at Tranquil Park. In partnership with the City of Wilsonville\, Frie
 nds of Trees is working to establish a diverse native forest that will impr
 ove wildlife habitat! </p><p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assi
 gned a planting crew. The planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, to
 ols\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/ho
 t chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather wearin
 g sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<br></p><p><b>How do I r
 egister? </b><span>Pre-Registration is now closed but planters are still ne
 eded\, just simply show up :)</span></p><p><strong>Parking Note:</strong>  
 Please be mindful of driveway\, there are several NO PARKING signs on SW Pa
 rkwood due to construction.<span></span></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We requ
 est that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and
  older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href=
 "http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth w
 aiver form</u></u></u></u></a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p>
 <p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsof
 trees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team is also happy to assist!  You can r
 each Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target
 ="_blank"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></
 a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting together soon!</p><p>===</p
 ><p>Thank you to our event sponsor <a href="https://portlandgeneral.com/" t
 arget="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Portland General Electric</u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></a>.</p><p>===</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnersh
