DESCRIPTION:========<br><b>Due to popular support\, this event is full and 
 closed</b>.  We hope to see you at another event!<br>========<br><br>Celebr
 ate Earth Week by digging in with Friends of Trees and the Greening Wilkes 
 coalition! Help is needed to mulch hundreds of native trees and shrubs that
  were planted this past winter at this special site in the Columbia Slough.
  We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time allows. <u>Not
 e: there will be no tree-planting at this event\, and this is physically-de
 manding work</u> (great for folks looking for a work out!).  Our stewardshi
 p events help to ensure the highest level of plant survival through the PNW
  dry summer months ahead.<br><u></u><p><b><u>Event Schedule:</u></b><br></p
 ><p></p><ul><li><b>Please arrive by 9:45am</b> to find our tent and sign-in
 \, stewardship activities start promptly at 10:00am. We provide gloves\, to
 ols\, and guidance. All you need to do is show up dressed for the weather a
 nd wearing sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) and be 
 ready to have fun!</li><li><b>12:45pm:</b> Stewardship activities end</li><
 li><b>1:00-2:00pm: </b>Lunch + Nature Walk + Native Plant Giveaway! Lunch i
 s provided at Wilkes City Park (1 block from the event site) followed by a 
 nature walk through the neighborhood\, led by Oregon Bird Alliance (formerl
 y Portland Audubon). And\, free native plants and trees will be available f
 or you to take home!  </li></ul><br><p></p><p><b>Under age 18?</b><span> We
  request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 1
 6 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to hand us a </span><b
 ><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u>
 <u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></b><span> sig
 ned by their parent/guardian.</span><br></p><p></p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pl
 <u></u>ease check out our <a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq
 /" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</
 u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a>.  Our team is also happy to 
 assist!  Reach us at <a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="
 _blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@fr<u></u>iendsoftrees.or
 <u></u>g</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a> We look forward to
  planting together soon!<br></p><hr /><p><span>T</span><span>his event is p
 art of a celebration organized by Greening Wilkes. Greening Wilkes is a col
 laborative project to engage the community surrounding Wilkes Park and Wilk
 es Natural Area to improve and diversify green spaces throughout the neighb
 orhood. Friends of Trees\, Verde\, Columbia Slough Watershed Council\, Port
 land Parks &amp\; Recreation\, and Oregon Bird Alliance (formally Portland 
 Audubon) have teamed up together to offer stewardship opportunities in Wilk
 es Creek Headwaters and Wilkes Creek Natural Area.  This event is also in c
 ollaboration with POIC.</span><br></p>
