 and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please c
 ome dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy\, closed-toe shoes and get r
 eady to have fun!\n\n<b>Due to popular community interest\, this event is n
 ow full and closed to unregistered groups of 5 people or more.</b> We encou
 rage groups to register for our similar King City Park planting this same d
 ate/time\, just 3 miles away.  RSVPs not required for individuals or groups
  of 4 or fewer -- you may simply show up!\n\nJoin Friends of Trees\, Tualat
 in Riverkeepers\, the City of Tigard and Clean Water Services at Cook Park.
