DESCRIPTION:After nearly a decade\, Friends of Trees is excited to be plant
 ing at the Sandy River Delta again!  Please arrive around 8:45am to be regi
 stered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. 
 We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, 
 tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy 
 shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested for groups o
 f more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org/voluntee
 r/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.   Please contact Jenny
  or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more informatio
 n. \n\nWe are partnering with the Sandy River Basin Watershed Council and F
 riends of the Sandy River Delta with support from East Multnomah Soil & Wat
 er Conservation District\, the US Forest Service\, PGE's Habitat Fund\, and
  the Jubitz Foundation.\n
