DESCRIPTION:Memorial Park is 126 acres and Wilsonville's largest park.  We 
 will be meeting near the community gardens on the north east side of the pa
 rk and planting along Boeckman Creek which is home to Chinook salmon\, stee
 lhead and Cutthroat trout.  We will be planting native trees and shrubs as 
 well as removing some invasive plants from the area.\n\nThis planting is in
  partnership with the City of Wilsonville.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am t
 o be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly at
  9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as 
 gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and wearin
 g sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly requested for
  groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftrees.org
 /volunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so. Please contac
 t Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need more inf
 ormation.\n
