DESCRIPTION:This planting is part of Johnson Creek Watershed Council's "Wat
 ershed Wide Event." Come plant native trees and shrubs to help restore the 
 Johnson Creek Watershed's native habitats\, increase water quality and redu
 ce the amount of stormwater entering the creek. Lunch will be provided at a
 n afternoon celebration event. \n\nThis project is in partnership with the 
 Johnson Creek Watershed Council and the City of Gresham and is supported by
  the East Multnomah Soil & Water Conservation District. \n\nPlease arrive a
 round 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will sta
 rt promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee
 \, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weat
 her and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are kindly
  requested for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.frie
 ndsoftrees.org/volunteer/group-registration-request-form>HERE</a> to do so.
   Please contact Jenny or Ian at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions o
 r need more information.
