DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><u></u><b>Thanks for con
 sidering signing-up to plant hundreds of native trees and shrubs along Ghos
 t Creek in North Plains!&nbsp\;</b><u></u><br><u></u><b><br></b>Please arri
 ve by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting start
 s at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as
  breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is sho
 w up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready t
 o have fun!<br><br><u></u><b>How do I register?</b>&nbsp\;Online registrati
 on has closed at this time\, but there is still room at this event!&nbsp\; 
 Please simply show up and sign-in when you arrive.<br><p><b>Under age 18?</
 b>&nbsp\;We request that youth 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardia
 n.&nbsp\; Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and will need to ha
 nd us a&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver"><u><u><
 u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;signed by their pa
 rent/guardian.</p><p><b>What about Covid-19?</b>&nbsp\;We&nbsp\;<u>require<
 /u>&nbsp\;that all people at our events cancel if you are feeling unwell or
  have been exposed to someone who tested positive for Covid-19 within 3 day
 s of the event.&nbsp\; We&nbsp\;<u>recommend&nbsp\;</u>everyone is fully-va
 ccinated\, bring and wear a face mask when working in close quarters\, and 
 respect 6’ of physical distance. Please see our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https:
 //friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer Frequently Asked
  Questions webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;for more details.&nbsp
 \; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><b>Questions?&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</b>Plea
 se check out our&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-
 faq/"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.&nbsp\;
  Our team is also happy to assist!&nbsp\; You can reach Gabriel and Jenny a
 t&nbsp\;<b><u><a href="mailto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org"><u><u><u><u>vol
 unteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>&nbsp\;We look forward
  to planting together soon!</p><b><hr></b><p><u></u>This event is in partne
 rship with Clean Water Services and<u></u>&nbsp\;part of Tree For All\, a p
 artnership which has planted more than ten million native plants in the Tua
 latin River Watershed since 2005! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\,
