DESCRIPTION:Help celebrate the MLK Weekend of Service with us!\n\nThis is o
 ur first event along the I-205 Multi-Use Path for 2013!  We will be plantin
 g a few replacement trees and re-mulching previously planted trees.  We are
  very excited to continue reforesting the transportation corridor that runs
  from the Columbia River in the North to the City of Gladstone in the south
 . Metro\, ODOT\, EMSWCD are partnering this season with Friends of Trees to
  increase livability\, habitat and air quality along the I-205 corridor. Th
 is planting is generously sponsored by REI.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am 
 to be registered and assigned to a crew. The planting will start promptly a
 t 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as
  gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come dressed for the weather and weari
 ng sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\n\nRSVPs are not required. Pleas
 e contact Andy or Jenny at (503) 595-0213 if you have any questions or need
  more information. We look forward to seeing you out there! 
