DESCRIPTION:<br>==============<br><br>Due to popular interest\, this Tree C
 are event is <b>full and closed</b>.&nbsp\; Thanks for your understanding\,
  and please consider joining one of our other open events that fits your sc
 hedule!<br><br>==============<br>Join Friends of Trees\, the City of Lake O
 swego\, and Friends of Luscher Farm in mulching Oregon White Oaks and other
  native trees and shrubs to help restore this important habitat area. Mulch
 ing these newly planted trees and shrubs helps to ensure the highest rates 
 of survival. We may also take out some weedy introduced plants\, if time al
 lows.&nbsp\; This project is part of a larger effort under way by the City 
 of Lake Oswego in partnership with Mosaic Ecology to improve the park's Oak
  Woodland.<br><br>There will be a short shuttle ride to the planting event 
 or you are welcome to take an approximately 10-minute walk along a paved pa
 th to the planting area.&nbsp\;<br><br>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in a
 nd enjoy some breakfast treats and coffee\, tea\, or hot chocolate. Tree Ca
 re activities start promptly at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and gui
 dance\, so all you need to do is show up dressed for the weather and wearin
 g sturdy shoes or boots (no sandals of any kind\, please!) â and be ready
  to have fun!<b><br></b><b><br><u>Under age 18?</u></b><u> </u>A signed <a 
 href="http://friendsoftrees.org/images/stories/pdf/Youth_Waiver_2015.pdf" t
 arget="_blank">youth waiver</a> is required for you to volunteer. We ask th
 at youth 15 years and younger are accompanied by an adult.<br><br>Please co
 ntact Jenny\, Pablo\, and Carey at (503) 595-0213 // <a href="mailto:volunt
 eer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank">volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</a> if
  you have questions or need any further information. We look forward to see
 ing you out there!
