DESCRIPTION:<p><b>=============</b></p><p><b>This event is Full &amp\; Clos
 ed. Please consider any of our other plantings.</b></p><p><b>============</
 b></p><p><br></p><p>Celebrate the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr by pl
 anting hundreds of trees and shrubs at Woodhaven Natural Area along Cedar C
 reek! This versatile site is a beloved neighborhood park\, a locally signif
 icant natural area\, and a provider of regional wildlife connectivity. </p>
 <p>Please arrive by 8:45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The 
 planting starts at 9:00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidanc
 e\, as well as breakfast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you nee
 d to do is show up dressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, 
 and be ready to have fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 
 15 and under volunteer with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volu
 nteer on their own and will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friends
 oftrees.org/youthwaiver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><
 u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u><
 /a></u></b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Pleas
 e check out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" t
 arget="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage
 </u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our team
  is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mailto:
 Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u><u
 ><u><u><b><u>volunteer@friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></u></u></u></
 u></u></u></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213.  We look forward to planting tog
 ether soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p>This event is in partnership with Clean Wate
 r Services and the City of Sherwood.</p>
