DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Friends of Trees is excited to partner with Portland OIC 
 and Portland Parks &amp\; Recreation to restore this two acre parcel of the
  Columbia Slough. </b>Help needed to plant hundreds of native shrubs and wi
 ldflowers at this important community site. </p><p>Please arrive by 9:45am 
 to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 10:00am.
  We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as breakfast s
 nacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up dressed
  for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have fun!<
 /p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunteer wit
 h a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own and wil
 l need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwaiver" t
