DESCRIPTION:Join us on this special Monday planting to help celebrate the M
 artin Luther King Jr. Day of Service!\n\nFriends of Trees in partnership wi
 th King City and and Clean Water Services will be planting native seedlings
  at King City Park. This planting is part of the Tree For All campaign whic
 h has planted over three million native plants in the Tualatin River Waters
 hed in the past decade! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, thousands
  of volunteers\, other non-profits\, city partners\, and private landowners
  will be working together this season to continue the success of this progr
 am.\n\nPlease arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a crew.
  The event will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snacks and h
 ot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Please come d
 ressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to have fun!\
 n\n<b>Due to high demand\, this event is now closed to future group sign-up
 s</b> Individuals or small groups of 4 or fewer are welcome to simply show 
 up.  Thank you for your interest and please consider joining us at another 
 of our planting events!\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 595-0213 
 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward to seei
 ng you out there!
