DESCRIPTION:<p>=======</p><p><b>Due to popular support\, this event is <u>f
 ull and closed</u></b>. Please consider a future event that still has room 
 -- we hope to plant with you soon!</p><p>=======</p><p>Bybee Lakes Hope Cen
 ter is a transitional housing facility in North Portland supporting people 
 experiencing homelessness. They have a 5 acre Victory Garden\, run by VETRe
 st with a young fruit orchard\, a thriving vegetable garden\, and a walking
  path with a variety of large stock trees planted by Friends of Trees in 20
 21. <b>For this event we are partnering with VETRest to plant hundreds of n
 ative trees and shrubs for residents to enjoy!</b></p><p>Please arrive by 9
 :45am to sign-in and be assigned a planting crew. The planting starts at 10
 :00am. We provide gloves\, tools\, and planting guidance\, as well as break
 fast snacks and coffee/tea/hot chocolate -- all you need to do is show up d
 ressed for the weather wearing sturdy shoes or boots\, and be ready to have
  fun!</p><p><b>Under age 18?</b> We request that youth 15 and under volunte
 er with a parent/guardian.  Youth 16 and older can volunteer on their own a
 nd will need to hand us a <b><u><a href="http://friendsoftrees.org/youthwai
 ver" target="_blank"><u><u><u><u>youth waiver form</u></u></u></u></a></u><
 /b> signed by their parent/guardian.</p><p><b>Questions?  </b>Please check 
 out our <b><u><a href="https://friendsoftrees.org/volunteer-faq/" target="_
 blank"><u><u><u><u>Volunteer FAQ webpage</u></u></u></u></a></u></b>.  Our 
 team is also happy to assist!  You can reach Cece and Jenny at <a href="mai
 lto:Volunteer@friendsoftrees.org" target="_blank"><u><u><u><b><u>volunteer@
 friendsoftrees.org</u></b></u></u></u></a>\, 503-595-0213. We look forward 
 to planting together soon!</p><b><hr /></b><p><br><br></p>
