DESCRIPTION:Please arrive around 8:45am to be registered and assigned to a 
 crew. The planting will start promptly at 9:00am. We provide breakfast snac
 ks and hot chocolate/coffee\, as well as gloves\, tools and guidance. Pleas
 e come dressed for the weather and wearing sturdy shoes and get ready to ha
 ve fun!\n\n<b>Looking to volunteer as a group?</b> RSVPs are kindly request
 ed for groups of more than 5 people - click <a href=http://www.friendsoftre
 es.org/volunteering/group-registration>HERE</a> to do so. RSVPs are not req
 uired for groups of 4 or less.\n\nPlease contact Jenny or Randi at (503) 59
 5-0213 if you have any questions or need more information. We look forward 
 to seeing you out there!\n\n<i>Friends of Trees is excited to continue our 
 partnership this season with the City of Durham and Clean Water Services. T
 his planting is part of the Tree For All campaign which strives to plant on
 e million native trees and shrubs during the 2014-2015 planting season with
 in the Tualatin River Watershed! Clean Water Services\, Friends of Trees\, 
 thousands of volunteers\, other non-profits\, City partners\, and private l
 andowners will all be working together to make this happen!</i>\n\n<i>This 
 event is generously sponsored by <b>Oregon Soap Company</b>.</I>\n\n
